{"parentUuid":"57a680d4-e74d-4cc4-8924-5c8993b01aad","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"eca00838-5098-4dde-983a-34e68a423bb3","agentId":"aa3971c3406bc34d2","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KHTK9Nx1PFwNEMVrFQeLEX","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tcriteria_total: 22\n3\tdelegated_criteria: [AC22]\n4\t---\n5\t\n6\t# Acceptance criteria — per-customer metric quotas\n7\t\n8\tDefinition-of-done for this feature. Implementation builds to these; testing maps each ID to a test\n9\t(`criteria_covered`); the deploy gate requires `criteria_covered.total == criteria_total` and that\n10\tevery delegated id appears in `delegated_criteria` (only `security` is a valid delegate). Derived\n11\tfrom `.pipeline/requirements.md` (authoritative) + `PROJECT.md`.\n12\t\n13\t| ID | Criterion | File / layer | How verified |\n14\t|---|---|---|---|\n15\t| AC1 | `PUT /v1/quotas` (admin key + valid body) creates a quota → **201**, response echoes `{customer_id, metric, limit_per_window}`, exactly one `quotas` row persisted | `src/api/routes/quotas.py`, `src/services/quota_service.py`, `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py` | `tests/integration/test_quotas_endpoint.py::test_put_creates_quota_returns_201_and_echoes` |\n16\t| AC2 | `PUT /v1/quotas` replacing an existing `(customer_id, metric)` → **200**, `limit_per_window` updated, still exactly one row (upsert, no duplicate) | `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py` (`xmax` insert/replace) | `tests/integration/test_quotas_endpoint.py::test_put_replace_returns_200_single_row` |\n17\t| AC3 | `PUT /v1/quotas` with an **ingest**-scoped key → **403**, envelope `code: forbidden`; admin scope required | `src/api/routes/quotas.py`, `src/auth/api_key.py` | `tests/integration/test_quotas_endpoint.py::test_ingest_key_forbidden` |\n18\t| AC4 | `PUT /v1/quotas` with missing/malformed/revoked auth → **401** | `src/auth/api_key.py` | `tests/integration/test_quotas_endpoint.py::test_put_requires_auth` |\n19\t| AC5 | Validation: `limit_per_window` = 0/negative/non-integer → **422** `validation_failed`; unknown field → 422 (`extra='forbid'`); `customer_id`/`metric` outside allowlist → 422 | `src/api/schemas/quotas.py` | `tests/test_schemas_quotas.py` + `tests/integration/test_quotas_endpoint.py::test_validation_rejections` |\n20\t| AC6 | Tenant isolation: a quota is stored under and enforced against the authenticated `api_key_id` only; a second tenant's key never reads/affects tenant A's quota (api_key_id scoping + RLS) | `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py`, `alembic/versions/0003_*`, `src/db/session.py` | `tests/integration/test_quotas_endpoint.py::test_quota_is_tenant_isolated` |\n21\t| AC7 | `POST /v1/events` for a `(customer, metric)` with **no quota** → unchanged behavior (201, unlimited); no regression | `src/services/events_service.py` | `tests/integration/test_events_quota_enforcement.py::test_no_quota_is_unlimited` |\n22\t| AC8 | `POST /v1/events` where `R + Q <= L` → **201** accepted, rollup increments normally | `src/services/events_service.py`, `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py` | `tests/integration/test_events_quota_enforcement.py::test_under_limit_accepted` |\n23\t| AC9 | `POST /v1/events` where `R + Q > L` → **429** envelope `code: quota_exceeded` + `Retry-After` header (seconds to next hour); **no event row persisted and rollup not incremented** (transaction rolled back) | `src/services/events_service.py`, `src/api/errors.py` | `tests/integration/test_events_quota_enforcement.py::test_over_limit_429_and_no_partial_write` |\n24\t| AC10 | `Q > L` against an **empty window** → **429** `quota_exceeded`; no rollup row created | `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py`, `src/services/events_service.py` | `tests/integration/test_events_quota_enforcement.py::test_empty_window_q_gt_l_rejected` |\n25\t| AC11 | Idempotent replay of a previously-**accepted** event, window now over quota → **200** replay of the original stored result; quota **not** consulted; no usage added | `src/services/events_service.py` | `tests/integration/test_events_quota_enforcement.py::test_replay_over_quota_returns_200_no_usage` |\n26\t| AC12 | A quota set/lowered **mid-window** takes effect immediately against the already-accumulated rollup (lowering `L <= R` blocks the rest of the window) | `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py` (fresh read per POST) | `tests/integration/test_events_quota_enforcement.py::test_midwindow_change_takes_effect` |\n27\t| AC13 | Strict enforcement under concurrency: N concurrent **distinct-idempotency-key** posts of `Q` against `L` never drive `usage_rollup.total_quantity` above `L`; the excess are rejected 429 | `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py` (`FOR UPDATE OF q`), `src/services/events_service.py` | `tests/integration/test_quota_concurrency.py::test_concurrent_posts_never_exceed_limit` |\n28\t| AC14 | Throttle precedence: the Tier-2 per-key throttle (`code: rate_limited`) still fires before any quota logic; quota rejection uses the **distinct** `code: quota_exceeded` | `src/api/routes/events.py`, `src/api/errors.py` | `tests/integration/test_events_quota_enforcement.py::test_throttle_precedes_quota_distinct_codes` |\n29\t| AC15 | `PUT /v1/quotas` is rate-limited by the **Tier-2 per-`api_key_id`** token bucket (principal-keyed, post-auth); two principals sharing one IP get independent buckets | `src/api/routes/quotas.py`, `src/auth/rate_limit.py` | `tests/integration/test_quotas_endpoint.py::test_put_rate_limited_per_principal` (two-principals-one-IP shape) |\n30\t| AC16 | Migration `0003` `up→down→up` restores schema + re-enforces all constraints (`quotas` PK/FK/`CHECK(limit>=1)`, `api_keys.scope CHECK IN ('ingest','admin')`); `quotas` is a create-migration (no row-survival across down); pre-existing `api_keys` rows survive the scope column add/drop (scope resets to `'ingest'` default — defined expand/contract behavior) | `alembic/versions/0003_*` | `tests/integration/test_quota_migration.py::test_0003_roundtrip_schema_and_constraints` |\n31\t| AC17 | `seed_api_key.py --admin` provisions a key with `scope='admin'`; without the flag `scope` defaults to `'ingest'` | `scripts/seed_api_key.py`, `src/repositories/api_keys_repo.py` | `tests/integration/test_seed_api_key_script.py::test_admin_flag_sets_scope` |\n32\t| AC18 | All new `quotas` SQL is parameterized (`text()` bind params only); an injection payload in `customer_id`/`metric` is rejected at the schema boundary (422) and never reaches the SQL sink | `src/api/schemas/quotas.py`, `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py` | `tests/integration/test_quotas_endpoint.py::test_injection_rejected_at_boundary` + security 6c (Semgrep) |\n33\t| AC19 | Observability/audit: a quota rejection logs `quota.rejected` (WARNING; `userId`, `action=deny`, `customer_id`, `metric`, `reason` — **no** usage totals); a quota upsert logs `quota.upsert` (`action=create|replace`, who/what/when); a scope-denied PUT logs `quota.forbidden` | `src/services/quota_service.py`, `src/services/events_service.py`, `src/api/routes/quotas.py` | `tests/integration/test_events_quota_enforcement.py::test_rejection_is_logged_without_totals` + `test_quotas_endpoint.py::test_upsert_and_forbidden_logged` |\n34\t| AC20 (perf) | `POST /v1/events` **p95 < 50 ms** under the sustained distributed-key k6 load **with quotas active** (high limits, no rejection) — the quota-check path does not blow the existing budget | `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py`, `src/services/events_service.py`; `tests/integration/k6/load_events_quota.js` | `tests/integration/test_perf_k6_load.py::test_events_ingest_with_quotas_p95_under_50ms` (nearest-rank p95 over raw k6 samples) |\n35\t| AC21 (DAST-readiness) | The served `/openapi.json` includes `PUT /v1/quotas` matching the implemented route/schema; the DAST auth context documents an **admin**-scoped seeded test key (`seed_api_key.py --admin`) with the `Authorization: Bearer mtr_live_<key_id>_<secret>` scheme | `src/api/routes/quotas.py`, `.pipeline/plan.md`, `docs/system_architecture.md` | `tests/test_dast_context_documented.py` + `tests/integration/test_quotas_endpoint.py::test_openapi_exposes_put_quotas` |\n36\t| AC22 | ASVS 5.0.0 L1/L2 (+ in-scope L3: V15.4.x safe concurrency, V11.2.4 constant-time) reconciliation across the change set — triggered chapters V1/V2/V4/V6/V8/V12/V13/V14/V15/V16 met or waived | security stage (`asvs` reconciliation block) | delegated: `security` (covered:false at the testing stage) |\n37\t\n38\tNotes:\n39\t- AC22 is **delegated to the security stage** (ASVS reconciliation is its deliverable, not a\n40\t  test-suite assertion) — declared in `delegated_criteria` above; testing marks it\n41\t  `covered: false, delegated: \"security\"`.\n42\t- AC20 is a measurable **performance** criterion (threshold p95 < 50 ms on `POST /v1/events`) —\n43\t  measured by testing's performance mode against the real k6 harness; it rides `criteria_covered`.\n44\t- No `data_protection` criterion is emitted: every new stored field is classified **non-sensitive\n45\t  operational config** (see plan *Data classification*), so no field-level KDF/KMS mechanism is\n46\t  required — `data_protection_waiver: all new stored fields (customer_id, metric, limit_per_window,\n47\t  scope) are non-sensitive opaque operational config already stored as identifiers; RDS SSE\n48\t  (storage-level) covers them`.\n49\t"}]},"uuid":"e9a578d8-ab45-4f0a-b3f3-7cb7121c5345","timestamp":"2026-07-08T18:03:15.494Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"57a680d4-e74d-4cc4-8924-5c8993b01aad","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"e9a578d8-ab45-4f0a-b3f3-7cb7121c5345","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa3971c3406bc34d2","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccq2jR9VjjoqpAAB2ZMnD","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me examine the existing codebase in depth to understand conventions before implementing."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6164,"cache_read_input_tokens":47608,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":6164,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccq2jQDS4rbA3dc8BWwv9","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"28100d6f-b45e-4da4-aec2-6d53d571ee33","timestamp":"2026-07-08T18:03:17.624Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"28100d6f-b45e-4da4-aec2-6d53d571ee33","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa3971c3406bc34d2","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccq2jR9VjjoqpAAB2ZMnD","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01VBB2BLSo2cZ1Bg7iw3HPW9","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\services\\events_service.py"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6164,"cache_read_input_tokens":47608,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":6164,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccq2jQDS4rbA3dc8BWwv9","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"b17951e7-8a0a-47c2-a0a6-0d335ef789d0","timestamp":"2026-07-08T18:03:19.011Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"b17951e7-8a0a-47c2-a0a6-0d335ef789d0","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"eca00838-5098-4dde-983a-34e68a423bb3","agentId":"aa3971c3406bc34d2","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VBB2BLSo2cZ1Bg7iw3HPW9","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t\"\"\"Service for `POST /v1/events` — the idempotent insert + rollup increment.\n2\t\n3\tOrchestrates one PostgreSQL transaction per request: try the insert, and only\n4\tif it actually landed a new row, upsert the rollup counter. This is the one\n5\ttransaction the plan's idempotency mechanism depends on for atomicity — see\n6\t`src/repositories/events_repo.py` for the `ON CONFLICT` primitive itself.\n7\t\"\"\"\n8\t\n9\tfrom dataclasses import dataclass\n10\tfrom datetime import datetime, timezone\n11\tfrom decimal import Decimal\n12\t\n13\tfrom src.api.schemas.events import EventCreateRequest, EventResponse\n14\tfrom src.auth.api_key import AuthenticatedPrincipal\n15\tfrom src.db.session import scoped_transaction\n16\tfrom src.logging import get_logger\n17\tfrom src.repositories.events_repo import (\n18\t    EventRecord,\n19\t    find_event_by_idempotency_key,\n20\t    increment_usage_rollup,\n21\t    insert_event_if_new,\n22\t)\n23\tfrom src.services.time_windows import floor_to_hour_utc\n24\t\n25\tlogger = get_logger(service=\"meterly\")\n26\t\n27\t\n28\t@dataclass(frozen=True)\n29\tclass EventCreationOutcome:\n30\t    \"\"\"The result of processing a `POST /v1/events` request: the event\n31\t    record and the HTTP status the route should return (201 new, 200 replay).\"\"\"\n32\t\n33\t    record: EventRecord\n34\t    http_status: int\n35\t    idempotent_replay: bool\n36\t\n37\t\n38\tclass IdempotencyRaceError(RuntimeError):\n39\t    \"\"\"Raised if a duplicate-key insert lost the race but the original row\n40\t    can't be found — should be unreachable given the UNIQUE constraint, but\n41\t    the service fails loudly rather than returning an empty response.\"\"\"\n42\t\n43\t\n44\tasync def create_event(\n45\t    principal: AuthenticatedPrincipal, payload: EventCreateRequest\n46\t) -> EventCreationOutcome:\n47\t    \"\"\"Record a metered event, idempotent on `(api_key_id, idempotency_key)`.\n48\t\n49\t    The server — never the client — sets `api_key_id` (from the authenticated\n50\t    principal) and `window_start` (the receive time floored to the UTC hour),\n51\t    which is the mass-assignment protection the plan calls out (ASVS 15.3.3).\n52\t    \"\"\"\n53\t    received_at = datetime.now(timezone.utc)\n54\t    window_start = floor_to_hour_utc(received_at)\n55\t\n56\t    async with scoped_transaction(principal.api_key_id) as session:\n57\t        inserted = await insert_event_if_new(\n58\t            session,\n59\t            api_key_id=principal.api_key_id,\n60\t            customer_id=payload.customer_id,\n61\t            metric=payload.metric,\n62\t            quantity=payload.quantity,\n63\t            idempotency_key=payload.idempotency_key,\n64\t            window_start=window_start,\n65\t        )\n66\t\n67\t        if inserted is not None:\n68\t            await increment_usage_rollup(\n69\t                session,\n70\t                api_key_id=principal.api_key_id,\n71\t                customer_id=inserted.customer_id,\n72\t                metric=inserted.metric,\n73\t                window_start=inserted.window_start,\n74\t                quantity=inserted.quantity,\n75\t            )\n76\t            logger.info(\n77\t                \"event.create\",\n78\t                userId=principal.api_key_id,\n79\t                action=\"create\",\n80\t                resource_id=inserted.id,\n81\t                idempotent_replay=False,\n82\t            )\n83\t            return EventCreationOutcome(record=inserted, http_status=201, idempotent_replay=False)\n84\t\n85\t        original = await find_event_by_idempotency_key(\n86\t            session, api_key_id=principal.api_key_id, idempotency_key=payload.idempotency_key\n87\t        )\n88\t        if original is None:\n89\t            raise IdempotencyRaceError(\n90\t                \"insert reported a conflict but the original row could not be found\"\n91\t            )\n92\t\n93\t        logger.info(\n94\t            \"event.create\",\n95\t            userId=principal.api_key_id,\n96\t            action=\"read\",\n97\t            resource_id=original.id,\n98\t            idempotent_replay=True,\n99\t        )\n100\t        return EventCreationOutcome(record=original, http_status=200, idempotent_replay=True)\n101\t\n102\t\n103\tdef to_response(outcome: EventCreationOutcome) -> EventResponse:\n104\t    \"\"\"Map the service outcome to the minimal public response shape (ASVS 15.3.1).\"\"\"\n105\t    record = outcome.record\n106\t    return EventResponse(\n107\t        event_id=record.id,\n108\t        customer_id=record.customer_id,\n109\t        metric=record.metric,\n110\t        quantity=Decimal(record.quantity),\n111\t        window_start=record.window_start.isoformat(),\n112\t        idempotent_replay=outcome.idempotent_replay,\n113\t    )\n114\t"}]},"uuid":"ee8eb138-58b7-456a-9450-729abdae74df","timestamp":"2026-07-08T18:03:19.053Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"b17951e7-8a0a-47c2-a0a6-0d335ef789d0","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"ee8eb138-58b7-456a-9450-729abdae74df","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa3971c3406bc34d2","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccq2jR9VjjoqpAAB2ZMnD","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01RTWESHGwTKwbf6gdcTa486","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\repositories\\events_repo.py"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6164,"cache_read_input_tokens":47608,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":6164,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccq2jQDS4rbA3dc8BWwv9","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"9d8bb2c4-d667-4674-ad34-da39d429763c","timestamp":"2026-07-08T18:03:19.443Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"9d8bb2c4-d667-4674-ad34-da39d429763c","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"eca00838-5098-4dde-983a-34e68a423bb3","agentId":"aa3971c3406bc34d2","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RTWESHGwTKwbf6gdcTa486","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t\"\"\"Repository for `events` + the `usage_rollup` increment — the idempotent\n2\tinsert-and-aggregate primitive at the core of `POST /v1/events`.\n3\t\n4\tEvery query here is scoped by the authenticated `api_key_id` (the row-level-\n5\tsecurity invariant from `code-standards`); the PostgreSQL RLS policy on both\n6\ttables is the backstop if this scoping were ever missing.\n7\t\"\"\"\n8\t\n9\tfrom dataclasses import dataclass\n10\tfrom datetime import datetime\n11\tfrom decimal import Decimal\n12\t\n13\tfrom sqlalchemy import text\n14\tfrom sqlalchemy.ext.asyncio import AsyncSession\n15\t\n16\t\n17\t@dataclass(frozen=True)\n18\tclass EventRecord:\n19\t    \"\"\"A row of `events`, the fields the service layer returns to the caller.\"\"\"\n20\t\n21\t    id: int\n22\t    api_key_id: int\n23\t    customer_id: str\n24\t    metric: str\n25\t    quantity: Decimal\n26\t    idempotency_key: str\n27\t    window_start: datetime\n28\t\n29\t\n30\tasync def insert_event_if_new(\n31\t    session: AsyncSession,\n32\t    *,\n33\t    api_key_id: int,\n34\t    customer_id: str,\n35\t    metric: str,\n36\t    quantity: Decimal,\n37\t    idempotency_key: str,\n38\t    window_start: datetime,\n39\t) -> EventRecord | None:\n40\t    \"\"\"Insert a new event row unless `(api_key_id, idempotency_key)` already\n41\t    exists; returns None when the row already existed (a duplicate replay).\n42\t\n43\t    The `UNIQUE (api_key_id, idempotency_key)` constraint + `ON CONFLICT DO\n44\t    NOTHING` is the sole source of truth for \"have I seen this key before?\" —\n45\t    evaluated atomically by PostgreSQL, so 50 concurrent identical requests\n46\t    produce exactly one winner (AC-CONCURRENCY) with no application-level lock.\n47\t    \"\"\"\n48\t    result = await session.execute(\n49\t        text(\n50\t            \"\"\"\n51\t            INSERT INTO events (\n52\t                api_key_id, customer_id, metric, quantity, idempotency_key, window_start\n53\t            )\n54\t            VALUES (\n55\t                :api_key_id, :customer_id, :metric, :quantity, :idempotency_key, :window_start\n56\t            )\n57\t            ON CONFLICT (api_key_id, idempotency_key) DO NOTHING\n58\t            RETURNING id, api_key_id, customer_id, metric, quantity, idempotency_key, window_start\n59\t            \"\"\"\n60\t        ),\n61\t        {\n62\t            \"api_key_id\": api_key_id,\n63\t            \"customer_id\": customer_id,\n64\t            \"metric\": metric,\n65\t            \"quantity\": quantity,\n66\t            \"idempotency_key\": idempotency_key,\n67\t            \"window_start\": window_start,\n68\t        },\n69\t    )\n70\t    row = result.mappings().first()\n71\t    if row is None:\n72\t        return None\n73\t    return EventRecord(**row)\n74\t\n75\t\n76\tasync def find_event_by_idempotency_key(\n77\t    session: AsyncSession, *, api_key_id: int, idempotency_key: str\n78\t) -> EventRecord | None:\n79\t    \"\"\"Fetch the original event for a duplicate `idempotency_key` replay.\n80\t\n81\t    Scoped by `api_key_id` first — an idempotency key is only ever unique\n82\t    within its owning tenant (plan's \"idempotency_key scope\" note), so this\n83\t    also doubles as the tenant-isolation guard for the replay read.\n84\t    \"\"\"\n85\t    result = await session.execute(\n86\t        text(\n87\t            \"\"\"\n88\t            SELECT id, api_key_id, customer_id, metric, quantity, idempotency_key, window_start\n89\t            FROM events\n90\t            WHERE api_key_id = :api_key_id AND idempotency_key = :idempotency_key\n91\t            \"\"\"\n92\t        ),\n93\t        {\"api_key_id\": api_key_id, \"idempotency_key\": idempotency_key},\n94\t    )\n95\t    row = result.mappings().first()\n96\t    if row is None:\n97\t        return None\n98\t    return EventRecord(**row)\n99\t\n100\t\n101\tasync def increment_usage_rollup(\n102\t    session: AsyncSession,\n103\t    *,\n104\t    api_key_id: int,\n105\t    customer_id: str,\n106\t    metric: str,\n107\t    window_start: datetime,\n108\t    quantity: Decimal,\n109\t) -> None:\n110\t    \"\"\"Upsert the hourly rollup counter for `(api_key_id, customer_id, metric,\n111\t    window_start)`, adding `quantity` and incrementing `event_count` by one.\n112\t\n113\t    Only called after `insert_event_if_new` returns a row (this request won\n114\t    the insert) — a duplicate replay must never reach here, which is exactly\n115\t    why duplicates never double-count (AC2).\n116\t    \"\"\"\n117\t    await session.execute(\n118\t        text(\n119\t            \"\"\"\n120\t            INSERT INTO usage_rollup (\n121\t                api_key_id, customer_id, metric, window_start, total_quantity, event_count, updated_at\n122\t            )\n123\t            VALUES (\n124\t                :api_key_id, :customer_id, :metric, :window_start, :quantity, 1, now()\n125\t            )\n126\t            ON CONFLICT (api_key_id, customer_id, metric, window_start) DO UPDATE SET\n127\t                total_quantity = usage_rollup.total_quantity + EXCLUDED.total_quantity,\n128\t                event_count = usage_rollup.event_count + 1,\n129\t                updated_at = now()\n130\t            \"\"\"\n131\t        ),\n132\t        {\n133\t            \"api_key_id\": api_key_id,\n134\t            \"customer_id\": customer_id,\n135\t            \"metric\": metric,\n136\t            \"window_start\": window_start,\n137\t            \"quantity\": quantity,\n138\t        },\n139\t    )\n140\t"}]},"uuid":"ef308ca2-d36a-4c18-8ac8-eb36e9fa4460","timestamp":"2026-07-08T18:03:19.479Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"9d8bb2c4-d667-4674-ad34-da39d429763c","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"ef308ca2-d36a-4c18-8ac8-eb36e9fa4460","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa3971c3406bc34d2","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccq2jR9VjjoqpAAB2ZMnD","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_018Z6EuYxuRNNGsQ891GbEB6","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\api\\schemas\\events.py"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6164,"cache_read_input_tokens":47608,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":6164,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccq2jQDS4rbA3dc8BWwv9","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"68c3c1c9-4854-4af7-8520-fc093580639e","timestamp":"2026-07-08T18:03:19.833Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"68c3c1c9-4854-4af7-8520-fc093580639e","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"eca00838-5098-4dde-983a-34e68a423bb3","agentId":"aa3971c3406bc34d2","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018Z6EuYxuRNNGsQ891GbEB6","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t\"\"\"Validation contract for `POST /v1/events`.\n2\t\n3\tEvery field the client may set is bounded by an anchored allowlist regex or a\n4\tstrict numeric range (`code-standards` input-validation invariant); `api_key_id`,\n5\t`event_time`, and `window_start` are deliberately absent from this schema — the\n6\tserver sets them from the authenticated principal and the receive time, never\n7\tfrom client input (ASVS 15.3.3 mass-assignment protection, threat T2/E3 in the\n8\tplan's STRIDE model).\n9\t\"\"\"\n10\t\n11\tfrom decimal import Decimal\n12\t\n13\tfrom pydantic import BaseModel, ConfigDict, condecimal, constr\n14\t\n15\tCustomerId = constr(pattern=r\"^[A-Za-z0-9_.:-]{1,128}$\")\n16\tMetric = constr(pattern=r\"^[A-Za-z0-9_.:-]{1,64}$\")\n17\tIdempotencyKey = constr(pattern=r\"^[A-Za-z0-9_-]{1,200}$\")\n18\tQuantity = condecimal(gt=Decimal(0), le=Decimal(\"1e12\"), max_digits=20, decimal_places=6)\n19\t\n20\t\n21\tclass EventCreateRequest(BaseModel):\n22\t    \"\"\"The client-supplied body of `POST /v1/events`.\n23\t\n24\t    `extra='forbid'` rejects any unknown field outright — this is the\n25\t    mass-assignment defense: even if a client sends `api_key_id` or\n26\t    `event_time`, the request is rejected rather than silently ignored, so\n27\t    there is no ambiguity about what the server actually used.\n28\t    \"\"\"\n29\t\n30\t    model_config = ConfigDict(extra=\"forbid\")\n31\t\n32\t    customer_id: CustomerId\n33\t    metric: Metric\n34\t    quantity: Quantity\n35\t    idempotency_key: IdempotencyKey\n36\t\n37\t\n38\tclass EventResponse(BaseModel):\n39\t    \"\"\"The minimal response field set for an event (ASVS 15.3.1) — never a raw ORM row.\"\"\"\n40\t\n41\t    model_config = ConfigDict(extra=\"forbid\")\n42\t\n43\t    event_id: int\n44\t    customer_id: str\n45\t    metric: str\n46\t    quantity: Decimal\n47\t    window_start: str\n48\t    idempotent_replay: bool\n49\t"}]},"uuid":"9e01510b-6789-4754-af5f-34004b808b31","timestamp":"2026-07-08T18:03:19.871Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"68c3c1c9-4854-4af7-8520-fc093580639e","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"9e01510b-6789-4754-af5f-34004b808b31","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa3971c3406bc34d2","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccq2jR9VjjoqpAAB2ZMnD","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_0114SHC4GCDpVKxUrhZHufG4","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\api\\routes\\events.py"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6164,"cache_read_input_tokens":47608,"output_tokens":388,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":6164},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":388,"cache_read_input_tokens":47608,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6164,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":6164,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccq2jQDS4rbA3dc8BWwv9","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"4a4f50fd-1482-4768-87a8-db0fe9681daf","timestamp":"2026-07-08T18:03:20.132Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"4a4f50fd-1482-4768-87a8-db0fe9681daf","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"eca00838-5098-4dde-983a-34e68a423bb3","agentId":"aa3971c3406bc34d2","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0114SHC4GCDpVKxUrhZHufG4","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t\"\"\"`POST /v1/events` — record a metered event, idempotent on `idempotency_key`.\n2\t\n3\tEdge behavior (security headers, CORS, body-size guard, Tier-1 throttle) is\n4\tinherited from the middleware stack; this route only wires\n5\tauth -> Tier-2 throttle -> schema validation -> service.\n6\t\"\"\"\n7\t\n8\tfrom fastapi import APIRouter, Depends, Request, Response\n9\t\n10\tfrom src.api.schemas.events import EventCreateRequest, EventResponse\n11\tfrom src.auth import require_api_key\n12\tfrom src.auth.api_key import AuthenticatedPrincipal\n13\tfrom src.auth.rate_limit import enforce_tier2_rate_limit\n14\tfrom src.services.events_service import create_event, to_response\n15\t\n16\trouter = APIRouter(tags=[\"events\"])\n17\t\n18\t\n19\tasync def _require_authenticated_and_throttled(\n20\t    request: Request, principal: AuthenticatedPrincipal = Depends(require_api_key)\n21\t) -> AuthenticatedPrincipal:\n22\t    \"\"\"Compose auth then the Tier-2 per-key throttle, in that order.\n23\t\n24\t    A single dependency function pins the ordering FastAPI resolves\n25\t    dependencies in: `require_api_key` must complete (and thus populate\n26\t    `principal`) before `enforce_tier2_rate_limit` can key its bucket on it.\n27\t    \"\"\"\n28\t    await enforce_tier2_rate_limit(request, principal)\n29\t    return principal\n30\t\n31\t\n32\t@router.post(\"/v1/events\", response_model=EventResponse, status_code=201)\n33\tasync def post_event(\n34\t    payload: EventCreateRequest,\n35\t    response: Response,\n36\t    principal: AuthenticatedPrincipal = Depends(_require_authenticated_and_throttled),\n37\t) -> EventResponse:\n38\t    \"\"\"Record `payload` as a new event, or return the original result if\n39\t    `idempotency_key` was already seen for this caller (200, no-op).\"\"\"\n40\t    outcome = await create_event(principal, payload)\n41\t    response.status_code = outcome.http_status\n42\t    return to_response(outcome)\n43\t"}]},"uuid":"bf3c9125-6243-4383-9a17-19d0f4895646","timestamp":"2026-07-08T18:03:20.171Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"4a4f50fd-1482-4768-87a8-db0fe9681daf","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"bf3c9125-6243-4383-9a17-19d0f4895646","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa3971c3406bc34d2","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccq2jmPQeqdcTaZkAP9he","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01QMq7kQ5Dq6GqaahUBAo6is","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\api\\errors.py"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5742,"cache_read_input_tokens":53772,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":5742,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":45,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccq2jkAEjYG1dD1mpL5gg","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"a36223e8-ff43-44ec-87c0-7c0dd4001ce4","timestamp":"2026-07-08T18:03:22.741Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"a36223e8-ff43-44ec-87c0-7c0dd4001ce4","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"eca00838-5098-4dde-983a-34e68a423bb3","agentId":"aa3971c3406bc34d2","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QMq7kQ5Dq6GqaahUBAo6is","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t\"\"\"The error-envelope facade — every exception a handler raises terminates\n2\there, at one centralized boundary, as the single response shape:\n3\t`{\"error\": {\"code\", \"message\", \"requestId\"}}`.\n4\t\n5\tNever leaks a stack trace, exception type, SQL, or internal path to the\n6\tclient (ASVS 16.5.1/16.5.3) — the detail is logged server-side and the client\n7\tgets a generic, stable `code` plus the `requestId` that ties a user report\n8\tback to the server log line.\n9\t\"\"\"\n10\t\n11\tfrom fastapi import FastAPI, HTTPException, Request, status\n12\tfrom fastapi.exceptions import RequestValidationError\n13\tfrom fastapi.responses import JSONResponse\n14\tfrom starlette.exceptions import HTTPException as StarletteHTTPException\n15\t\n16\tfrom src.logging import get_logger\n17\t\n18\tlogger = get_logger(service=\"meterly\")\n19\t\n20\t_STATUS_TO_CODE = {\n21\t    status.HTTP_400_BAD_REQUEST: \"bad_request\",\n22\t    status.HTTP_401_UNAUTHORIZED: \"unauthorized\",\n23\t    status.HTTP_403_FORBIDDEN: \"forbidden\",\n24\t    status.HTTP_404_NOT_FOUND: \"not_found\",\n25\t    status.HTTP_409_CONFLICT: \"conflict\",\n26\t    status.HTTP_413_REQUEST_ENTITY_TOO_LARGE: \"payload_too_large\",\n27\t    status.HTTP_422_UNPROCESSABLE_ENTITY: \"validation_failed\",\n28\t    status.HTTP_429_TOO_MANY_REQUESTS: \"rate_limited\",\n29\t}\n30\t\n31\t\n32\tdef _request_id(request: Request) -> str:\n33\t    \"\"\"Read the correlation id the logging middleware assigned to this request.\"\"\"\n34\t    return getattr(request.state, \"request_id\", \"unknown\")\n35\t\n36\t\n37\tdef _envelope(code: str, message: str, request_id: str) -> dict:\n38\t    \"\"\"Build the one response shape every error returns.\"\"\"\n39\t    return {\"error\": {\"code\": code, \"message\": message, \"requestId\": request_id}}\n40\t\n41\t\n42\tdef register_error_handlers(app: FastAPI) -> None:\n43\t    \"\"\"Register the centralized exception handlers on `app`.\n44\t\n45\t    Called once from `src/main.py` at app construction — no route ever builds\n46\t    its own error response; it raises and lets this boundary map it.\n47\t    \"\"\"\n48\t\n49\t    @app.exception_handler(RequestValidationError)\n50\t    async def handle_validation_error(request: Request, exc: RequestValidationError) -> JSONResponse:\n51\t        \"\"\"Map Pydantic/FastAPI validation failures to 422 with a safe message.\"\"\"\n52\t        request_id = _request_id(request)\n53\t        logger.warning(\n54\t            \"validation.failed\",\n55\t            requestId=request_id,\n56\t            endpoint=request.url.path,\n57\t            errorCount=len(exc.errors()),\n58\t        )\n59\t        return JSONResponse(\n60\t            status_code=status.HTTP_422_UNPROCESSABLE_ENTITY,\n61\t            content=_envelope(\"validation_failed\", \"the request failed validation\", request_id),\n62\t        )\n63\t\n64\t    @app.exception_handler(StarletteHTTPException)\n65\t    async def handle_http_exception(request: Request, exc: StarletteHTTPException) -> JSONResponse:\n66\t        \"\"\"Map a raised `HTTPException` (auth, rate-limit, not-found, ...) to the envelope.\"\"\"\n67\t        request_id = _request_id(request)\n68\t        code = _STATUS_TO_CODE.get(exc.status_code, \"error\")\n69\t        message = exc.detail if isinstance(exc.detail, str) else \"request failed\"\n70\t        return JSONResponse(\n71\t            status_code=exc.status_code,\n72\t            content=_envelope(code, message, request_id),\n73\t            headers=getattr(exc, \"headers\", None) or {},\n74\t        )\n75\t\n76\t    @app.exception_handler(Exception)\n77\t    async def handle_unexpected_error(request: Request, exc: Exception) -> JSONResponse:\n78\t        \"\"\"Catch-all: log the full detail server-side, return a generic 500 to the client.\n79\t\n80\t        This is the fail-closed boundary — an unhandled exception mid-write\n81\t        never leaks stack/SQL/secret detail, and because the events + rollup\n82\t        write happens in one transaction (`src/services/events_service.py`),\n83\t        an exception here means that transaction was rolled back, not\n84\t        partially applied.\n85\t        \"\"\"\n86\t        request_id = _request_id(request)\n87\t        logger.error(\n88\t            \"request.unhandled_error\",\n89\t            requestId=request_id,\n90\t            endpoint=request.url.path,\n91\t            **{\"error.type\": type(exc).__name__, \"error.message\": str(exc)},\n92\t            exc_info=True,\n93\t        )\n94\t        return JSONResponse(\n95\t            status_code=status.HTTP_500_INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR,\n96\t            content=_envelope(\"internal\", \"an internal error occurred\", request_id),\n97\t        )\n98\t\n99\t\n100\t__all__ = [\"register_error_handlers\", \"HTTPException\"]\n101\t"}]},"uuid":"9a540336-3081-49f1-999d-766600a13ea8","timestamp":"2026-07-08T18:03:22.784Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"a36223e8-ff43-44ec-87c0-7c0dd4001ce4","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"9a540336-3081-49f1-999d-766600a13ea8","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa3971c3406bc34d2","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccq2jmPQeqdcTaZkAP9he","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01V2QP9xZvS9gZSyce7VRWnt","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\auth\\api_key.py"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5742,"cache_read_input_tokens":53772,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":5742,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":45,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccq2jkAEjYG1dD1mpL5gg","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"3b0c82e3-6fb0-4f8c-8d42-361834cc321e","timestamp":"2026-07-08T18:03:23.481Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"3b0c82e3-6fb0-4f8c-8d42-361834cc321e","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"eca00838-5098-4dde-983a-34e68a423bb3","agentId":"aa3971c3406bc34d2","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01V2QP9xZvS9gZSyce7VRWnt","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t\"\"\"Split-token API-key parsing and Argon2id verification against `api_keys`.\n2\t\n3\tKey format: `mtr_live_<key_id>_<secret>` — `key_id` is a public, indexed lookup\n4\thandle; `secret` is a >=128-bit CSPRNG value whose Argon2id hash is the only\n5\tthing stored. Parsing is a strict anchored regex so a malformed header is\n6\trejected before any database work (`src/api/schemas` sibling contract for the\n7\t`Authorization` header, per the plan's validation-contract table).\n8\t\"\"\"\n9\t\n10\timport re\n11\timport secrets\n12\tfrom dataclasses import dataclass\n13\t\n14\tfrom sqlalchemy.ext.asyncio import AsyncConnection\n15\t\n16\tfrom src.crypto import hash_secret, verify_secret\n17\tfrom src.repositories.api_keys_repo import find_active_key_by_key_id\n18\t\n19\t_TOKEN_PATTERN = re.compile(r\"^mtr_live_(?P<key_id>[A-Za-z0-9]{1,32})_(?P<secret>[A-Za-z0-9]{1,64})$\")\n20\t_KEY_ID_BYTES = 16\n21\t_SECRET_BYTES = 32\n22\t\n23\t\n24\t@dataclass(frozen=True)\n25\tclass ParsedApiKey:\n26\t    \"\"\"The two halves of a presented split-token API key.\"\"\"\n27\t\n28\t    key_id: str\n29\t    secret: str\n30\t\n31\t\n32\t@dataclass(frozen=True)\n33\tclass AuthenticatedPrincipal:\n34\t    \"\"\"The authenticated caller: the internal `api_key_id` and its rate-limit budget.\"\"\"\n35\t\n36\t    api_key_id: int\n37\t    rate_limit_per_sec: int\n38\t\n39\t\n40\tdef parse_split_token(presented_key: str) -> ParsedApiKey | None:\n41\t    \"\"\"Parse `mtr_live_<key_id>_<secret>`; returns None for anything malformed.\n42\t\n43\t    A strict, anchored regex means a malformed token is rejected before any\n44\t    database work — no scanning, no partial parse (401 before any DB work).\n45\t    \"\"\"\n46\t    match = _TOKEN_PATTERN.match(presented_key)\n47\t    if match is None:\n48\t        return None\n49\t    return ParsedApiKey(key_id=match.group(\"key_id\"), secret=match.group(\"secret\"))\n50\t\n51\t\n52\tasync def verify_api_key(\n53\t    connection: AsyncConnection, presented_key: str\n54\t) -> AuthenticatedPrincipal | None:\n55\t    \"\"\"Verify a presented `Authorization` bearer value end to end.\n56\t\n57\t    Parses the split token, looks the key up by its public `key_id`, and runs\n58\t    an Argon2id verify against the stored hash. Returns None on any failure —\n59\t    malformed token, unknown/revoked key_id, or a wrong secret are all\n60\t    indistinguishable to the caller (no oracle for key enumeration).\n61\t    \"\"\"\n62\t    parsed = parse_split_token(presented_key)\n63\t    if parsed is None:\n64\t        return None\n65\t\n66\t    record = await find_active_key_by_key_id(connection, parsed.key_id)\n67\t    if record is None:\n68\t        return None\n69\t\n70\t    if not verify_secret(parsed.secret, record.secret_hash):\n71\t        return None\n72\t\n73\t    return AuthenticatedPrincipal(\n74\t        api_key_id=record.id, rate_limit_per_sec=record.rate_limit_per_sec\n75\t    )\n76\t\n77\t\n78\tdef generate_split_token() -> tuple[str, str, str]:\n79\t    \"\"\"Generate a new `(key_id, secret, presented_key)` triple for key\n80\t    provisioning (`scripts/seed_api_key.py`).\n81\t\n82\t    `secret_hash = hash_secret(secret)` is what the caller stores; `secret`\n83\t    and the full `presented_key` are shown to the operator exactly once and\n84\t    never persisted in plaintext.\n85\t    \"\"\"\n86\t    key_id = secrets.token_hex(_KEY_ID_BYTES)\n87\t    secret = secrets.token_hex(_SECRET_BYTES)\n88\t    presented_key = f\"mtr_live_{key_id}_{secret}\"\n89\t    return key_id, secret, presented_key\n90\t\n91\t\n92\tdef hash_new_secret(secret: str) -> str:\n93\t    \"\"\"Hash a freshly generated secret for storage — thin re-export of the\n94\t    crypto facade so callers of this module don't need a second import.\"\"\"\n95\t    return hash_secret(secret)\n96\t"}]},"uuid":"17c3faae-3055-47cd-aa02-43546cfcf68e","timestamp":"2026-07-08T18:03:23.512Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"3b0c82e3-6fb0-4f8c-8d42-361834cc321e","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"17c3faae-3055-47cd-aa02-43546cfcf68e","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa3971c3406bc34d2","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccq2jmPQeqdcTaZkAP9he","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01APo4j4vp8Ws2fjw39d53oQ","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\repositories\\api_keys_repo.py"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5742,"cache_read_input_tokens":53772,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":5742,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":45,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccq2jkAEjYG1dD1mpL5gg","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"5ee673c4-abff-4e42-8679-ebe8e8692746","timestamp":"2026-07-08T18:03:23.852Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"5ee673c4-abff-4e42-8679-ebe8e8692746","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"eca00838-5098-4dde-983a-34e68a423bb3","agentId":"aa3971c3406bc34d2","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01APo4j4vp8Ws2fjw39d53oQ","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t\"\"\"Repository for `api_keys` — the split-token lookup by `key_id`.\n2\t\n3\tThis is the one repository that legitimately queries by something other than\n4\t`api_key_id` (it is *how* `api_key_id` gets resolved from a presented token),\n5\tso it is exempt from the row-level-security scoping rule the other\n6\trepositories enforce — there is no tenant scope yet at this point in the\n7\trequest.\n8\t\"\"\"\n9\t\n10\tfrom dataclasses import dataclass\n11\t\n12\tfrom sqlalchemy import text\n13\tfrom sqlalchemy.ext.asyncio import AsyncConnection\n14\t\n15\t\n16\t@dataclass(frozen=True)\n17\tclass ApiKeyRecord:\n18\t    \"\"\"A row from `api_keys`, the fields the auth guard needs to verify a request.\"\"\"\n19\t\n20\t    id: int\n21\t    key_id: str\n22\t    secret_hash: str\n23\t    rate_limit_per_sec: int\n24\t    revoked_at: object | None\n25\t\n26\t\n27\tasync def find_active_key_by_key_id(\n28\t    connection: AsyncConnection, key_id: str\n29\t) -> ApiKeyRecord | None:\n30\t    \"\"\"Look up a non-revoked API key by its public `key_id` handle.\n31\t\n32\t    Returns None if no matching, non-revoked key exists — the caller (the\n33\t    auth guard) treats that identically to a failed secret verification so\n34\t    key enumeration can't be distinguished from a wrong secret.\n35\t    \"\"\"\n36\t    result = await connection.execute(\n37\t        text(\n38\t            \"\"\"\n39\t            SELECT id, key_id, secret_hash, rate_limit_per_sec, revoked_at\n40\t            FROM api_keys\n41\t            WHERE key_id = :key_id AND revoked_at IS NULL\n42\t            \"\"\"\n43\t        ),\n44\t        {\"key_id\": key_id},\n45\t    )\n46\t    row = result.mappings().first()\n47\t    if row is None:\n48\t        return None\n49\t    return ApiKeyRecord(\n50\t        id=row[\"id\"],\n51\t        key_id=row[\"key_id\"],\n52\t        secret_hash=row[\"secret_hash\"],\n53\t        rate_limit_per_sec=row[\"rate_limit_per_sec\"],\n54\t        revoked_at=row[\"revoked_at\"],\n55\t    )\n56\t\n57\t\n58\tasync def create_api_key(\n59\t    connection: AsyncConnection,\n60\t    *,\n61\t    key_id: str,\n62\t    secret_hash: str,\n63\t    label: str,\n64\t    rate_limit_per_sec: int = 100,\n65\t) -> int:\n66\t    \"\"\"Insert a new API key row (secret already hashed by the caller) and\n67\t    return its internal surrogate id. Used only by `scripts/seed_api_key.py`\n68\t    — there is no key-creation HTTP endpoint in this build's scope.\n69\t    \"\"\"\n70\t    result = await connection.execute(\n71\t        text(\n72\t            \"\"\"\n73\t            INSERT INTO api_keys (key_id, secret_hash, label, rate_limit_per_sec)\n74\t            VALUES (:key_id, :secret_hash, :label, :rate_limit_per_sec)\n75\t            RETURNING id\n76\t            \"\"\"\n77\t        ),\n78\t        {\n79\t            \"key_id\": key_id,\n80\t            \"secret_hash\": secret_hash,\n81\t            \"label\": label,\n82\t            \"rate_limit_per_sec\": rate_limit_per_sec,\n83\t        },\n84\t    )\n85\t    return result.scalar_one()\n86\t"}]},"uuid":"16b3e750-23ed-4c6f-b050-c756f9baaf26","timestamp":"2026-07-08T18:03:23.870Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"5ee673c4-abff-4e42-8679-ebe8e8692746","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"16b3e750-23ed-4c6f-b050-c756f9baaf26","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa3971c3406bc34d2","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccq2jmPQeqdcTaZkAP9he","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01QngNWAeaE7ThtPzADSi9RB","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\auth\\rate_limit.py"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5742,"cache_read_input_tokens":53772,"output_tokens":364,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":5742},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":364,"cache_read_input_tokens":53772,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5742,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":5742,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccq2jkAEjYG1dD1mpL5gg","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"30b58411-bb3e-4056-ba75-63383e858cc2","timestamp":"2026-07-08T18:03:24.159Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"30b58411-bb3e-4056-ba75-63383e858cc2","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"eca00838-5098-4dde-983a-34e68a423bb3","agentId":"aa3971c3406bc34d2","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QngNWAeaE7ThtPzADSi9RB","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t\"\"\"Redis-backed token-bucket rate limiting — Tier 1 (pre-auth, IP+route) and\n2\tTier 2 (post-auth, per-`api_key_id`).\n3\t\n4\tState lives in Redis, never in-process: an in-process counter is per-task and\n5\tfails open behind the ALB once there is more than one Fargate task\n6\t(`api-edge-conventions`). The bucket check-and-decrement is a single atomic\n7\tLua script so concurrent requests against the same bucket can't race past the\n8\tlimit (the same TOCTOU concern the events idempotency mechanism addresses,\n9\tapplied to a counter instead of a unique constraint).\n10\t\"\"\"\n11\t\n12\tfrom dataclasses import dataclass\n13\t\n14\timport redis.asyncio as redis\n15\t\n16\tfrom src.config.settings import get_settings\n17\tfrom src.logging import get_logger\n18\t\n19\t# Atomic token-bucket refill + consume: KEYS[1] = bucket key.\n20\t# ARGV: capacity, refill_rate_per_second, now_ms, cost.\n21\t# Returns {allowed (0/1), tokens_remaining, retry_after_ms}.\n22\t_TOKEN_BUCKET_LUA = \"\"\"\n23\tlocal key = KEYS[1]\n24\tlocal capacity = tonumber(ARGV[1])\n25\tlocal refill_rate = tonumber(ARGV[2])\n26\tlocal now_ms = tonumber(ARGV[3])\n27\tlocal cost = tonumber(ARGV[4])\n28\t\n29\tlocal bucket = redis.call('HMGET', key, 'tokens', 'updated_at')\n30\tlocal tokens = tonumber(bucket[1])\n31\tlocal updated_at = tonumber(bucket[2])\n32\t\n33\tif tokens == nil then\n34\t  tokens = capacity\n35\t  updated_at = now_ms\n36\tend\n37\t\n38\tlocal elapsed_seconds = math.max(0, (now_ms - updated_at) / 1000)\n39\ttokens = math.min(capacity, tokens + elapsed_seconds * refill_rate)\n40\t\n41\tlocal allowed = 0\n42\tlocal retry_after_ms = 0\n43\tif tokens >= cost then\n44\t  tokens = tokens - cost\n45\t  allowed = 1\n46\telse\n47\t  local deficit = cost - tokens\n48\t  retry_after_ms = math.ceil((deficit / refill_rate) * 1000)\n49\tend\n50\t\n51\tredis.call('HMSET', key, 'tokens', tokens, 'updated_at', now_ms)\n52\tredis.call('PEXPIRE', key, 60000)\n53\t\n54\treturn {allowed, tostring(tokens), retry_after_ms}\n55\t\"\"\"\n56\t\n57\t\n58\t@dataclass(frozen=True)\n59\tclass RateLimitDecision:\n60\t    \"\"\"The outcome of a rate-limit check: whether the request is allowed and,\n61\t    if not, how long the caller should wait before retrying.\"\"\"\n62\t\n63\t    allowed: bool\n64\t    retry_after_seconds: float\n65\t\n66\t\n67\tclass RedisTokenBucketLimiter:\n68\t    \"\"\"A shared, atomic Redis token-bucket limiter used by both throttle tiers.\n69\t\n70\t    Each tier instantiates this with its own key prefix and capacity/refill\n71\t    policy; the Lua script guarantees the check-then-decrement is race-free\n72\t    across concurrently arriving requests and across Fargate tasks.\n73\t    \"\"\"\n74\t\n75\t    def __init__(self, redis_client: redis.Redis, *, key_prefix: str) -> None:\n76\t        self._redis = redis_client\n77\t        self._key_prefix = key_prefix\n78\t        self._script = self._redis.register_script(_TOKEN_BUCKET_LUA)\n79\t\n80\t    async def check(\n81\t        self, bucket_identity: str, *, capacity: int, refill_rate_per_second: float, cost: float = 1.0\n82\t    ) -> RateLimitDecision:\n83\t        \"\"\"Consume `cost` tokens from `bucket_identity`'s bucket; returns the decision.\"\"\"\n84\t        import time\n85\t\n86\t        now_ms = int(time.time() * 1000)\n87\t        allowed, _tokens_remaining, retry_after_ms = await self._script(\n88\t            keys=[f\"{self._key_prefix}:{bucket_identity}\"],\n89\t            args=[capacity, refill_rate_per_second, now_ms, cost],\n90\t        )\n91\t        return RateLimitDecision(\n92\t            allowed=bool(int(allowed)), retry_after_seconds=round(int(retry_after_ms) / 1000, 3)\n93\t        )\n94\t\n95\t\n96\t_redis_client: redis.Redis | None = None\n97\t_tier1_limiter: RedisTokenBucketLimiter | None = None\n98\t_tier2_limiter: RedisTokenBucketLimiter | None = None\n99\t\n100\t\n101\tdef get_redis_client() -> redis.Redis:\n102\t    \"\"\"Return the process-wide async Redis client, creating it on first use\n103\t    (deferred, like the DB engine, so import stays dependency-free).\"\"\"\n104\t    global _redis_client\n105\t    if _redis_client is None:\n106\t        _redis_client = redis.from_url(get_settings().redis_url, decode_responses=True)\n107\t    return _redis_client\n108\t\n109\t\n110\tdef get_tier1_limiter() -> RedisTokenBucketLimiter:\n111\t    \"\"\"Return the Tier-1 (pre-auth, IP+route-keyed) limiter singleton.\"\"\"\n112\t    global _tier1_limiter\n113\t    if _tier1_limiter is None:\n114\t        _tier1_limiter = RedisTokenBucketLimiter(get_redis_client(), key_prefix=\"ratelimit:tier1\")\n115\t    return _tier1_limiter\n116\t\n117\t\n118\tdef get_tier2_limiter() -> RedisTokenBucketLimiter:\n119\t    \"\"\"Return the Tier-2 (post-auth, `api_key_id`-keyed) limiter singleton.\"\"\"\n120\t    global _tier2_limiter\n121\t    if _tier2_limiter is None:\n122\t        _tier2_limiter = RedisTokenBucketLimiter(get_redis_client(), key_prefix=\"ratelimit:tier2\")\n123\t    return _tier2_limiter\n124\t\n125\t\n126\tasync def dispose_redis_client() -> None:\n127\t    \"\"\"Close the Redis client (called from lifespan shutdown).\"\"\"\n128\t    global _redis_client, _tier1_limiter, _tier2_limiter\n129\t    if _redis_client is not None:\n130\t        await _redis_client.aclose()\n131\t    _redis_client = None\n132\t    _tier1_limiter = None\n133\t    _tier2_limiter = None\n134\t\n135\t\n136\tasync def enforce_tier2_rate_limit(request: \"Request\", principal: \"AuthenticatedPrincipal\") -> None:\n137\t    \"\"\"Tier-2 dependency: enforce the caller's per-`api_key_id` token bucket.\n138\t\n139\t    Registered on a dependency that runs strictly **after** `require_api_key`\n140\t    (both endpoint routes depend on this ordering), so the bucket key is\n141\t    always the authenticated principal, never the client IP — this is the\n142\t    property the two-principals-one-IP test verifies (AC14/AC16).\n143\t\n144\t    Fails **open** (logs a warning, allows the request) on a Redis connection\n145\t    error — a cache outage degrading every authenticated call to \"temporarily\n146\t    unlimited\" is preferable to a full ingest outage; the durable UNIQUE-\n147\t    constraint/transaction guarantees are unaffected either way.\n148\t    \"\"\"\n149\t    from fastapi import HTTPException, status\n150\t\n151\t    try:\n152\t        decision = await get_tier2_limiter().check(\n153\t            str(principal.api_key_id),\n154\t            capacity=principal.rate_limit_per_sec,\n155\t            refill_rate_per_second=principal.rate_limit_per_sec,\n156\t        )\n157\t    except Exception:  # noqa: BLE001 - a Redis outage must not take down the whole API\n158\t        get_logger(service=\"meterly\").warning(\n159\t            \"ratelimit.backend_unavailable\", endpoint=request.url.path, tier=\"tier2\"\n160\t        )\n161\t        return\n162\t\n163\t    if not decision.allowed:\n164\t        get_logger(service=\"meterly\").warning(\n165\t            \"ratelimit.exceeded\",\n166\t            userId=principal.api_key_id,\n167\t            action=\"deny\",\n168\t            endpoint=request.url.path,\n169\t            reason=\"tier2_bucket_exhausted\",\n170\t        )\n171\t        raise HTTPException(\n172\t            status_code=status.HTTP_429_TOO_MANY_REQUESTS,\n173\t            detail=\"rate limit exceeded\",\n174\t            headers={\"Retry-After\": str(max(1, int(decision.retry_after_seconds) or 1))},\n175\t        )\n176\t"}]},"uuid":"38bccfb9-ebc7-4427-acb0-b27534fb3cf2","timestamp":"2026-07-08T18:03:24.197Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"30b58411-bb3e-4056-ba75-63383e858cc2","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"38bccfb9-ebc7-4427-acb0-b27534fb3cf2","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa3971c3406bc34d2","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccq2k4XHnYYTrDHRLdpCJ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me look at db/session.py, main.py, middleware.py, migrations (0001, 0002), usage_repo/usage_service, and the auth `__init__.py` for require_api_key."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8028,"cache_read_input_tokens":59514,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":8028,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":7,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccq2k3Q59GfUYMeXzRgEK","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"01457080-1bc4-4ae8-9e0a-6f2c68bfa8e8","timestamp":"2026-07-08T18:03:27.261Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"01457080-1bc4-4ae8-9e0a-6f2c68bfa8e8","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa3971c3406bc34d2","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccq2k4XHnYYTrDHRLdpCJ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01FwidjhUH9HSzFRUnQr5C3H","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\db\\session.py"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8028,"cache_read_input_tokens":59514,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":8028,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":7,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccq2k3Q59GfUYMeXzRgEK","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"5a3e3972-d9bc-4018-a3e4-f074b1c50be3","timestamp":"2026-07-08T18:03:27.970Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"5a3e3972-d9bc-4018-a3e4-f074b1c50be3","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"eca00838-5098-4dde-983a-34e68a423bb3","agentId":"aa3971c3406bc34d2","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FwidjhUH9HSzFRUnQr5C3H","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t\"\"\"Async database engine/session management.\n2\t\n3\tThe engine is created lazily (on first use / at lifespan startup), never at\n4\timport time — this is what lets `import src.main` succeed in the smoke-check\n5\tbuild-fallback mode with no database reachable. Every request runs inside a\n6\ttransaction that sets `app.current_api_key_id` via `SET LOCAL`, which backs the\n7\tPostgreSQL row-level-security policy on `events`/`usage_rollup` (defense in\n8\tdepth behind the application-level `api_key_id` scoping every repository query\n9\talready applies).\n10\t\"\"\"\n11\t\n12\tfrom collections.abc import AsyncIterator\n13\tfrom contextlib import asynccontextmanager\n14\t\n15\tfrom sqlalchemy.ext.asyncio import AsyncEngine, AsyncSession, async_sessionmaker, create_async_engine\n16\t\n17\tfrom src.config.secrets import get_database_url\n18\t\n19\t_engine: AsyncEngine | None = None\n20\t_session_factory: async_sessionmaker[AsyncSession] | None = None\n21\t\n22\t\n23\tdef get_engine() -> AsyncEngine:\n24\t    \"\"\"Return the process-wide async engine, creating it on first call.\n25\t\n26\t    Deferred creation (rather than at import time) keeps `import src.main`\n27\t    dependency-free for the smoke-check build-fallback path.\n28\t    \"\"\"\n29\t    global _engine\n30\t    if _engine is None:\n31\t        _engine = create_async_engine(\n32\t            get_database_url(),\n33\t            pool_pre_ping=True,\n34\t            pool_size=10,\n35\t            max_overflow=5,\n36\t        )\n37\t    return _engine\n38\t\n39\t\n40\tdef get_session_factory() -> async_sessionmaker[AsyncSession]:\n41\t    \"\"\"Return the process-wide session factory, creating it on first call.\"\"\"\n42\t    global _session_factory\n43\t    if _session_factory is None:\n44\t        _session_factory = async_sessionmaker(get_engine(), expire_on_commit=False)\n45\t    return _session_factory\n46\t\n47\t\n48\t@asynccontextmanager\n49\tasync def scoped_transaction(api_key_id: int) -> AsyncIterator[AsyncSession]:\n50\t    \"\"\"Open a transaction scoped to the authenticated `api_key_id`.\n51\t\n52\t    Sets `app.current_api_key_id` with `SET LOCAL` at the start of the\n53\t    transaction so the PostgreSQL RLS policy backstop applies even if a\n54\t    repository query were ever missing its own `api_key_id` filter. The\n55\t    setting is transaction-local and is discarded automatically on commit/\n56\t    rollback.\n57\t    \"\"\"\n58\t    session_factory = get_session_factory()\n59\t    async with session_factory() as session, session.begin():\n60\t        await session.execute(\n61\t            _set_local_statement(),\n62\t            {\"api_key_id\": str(api_key_id)},\n63\t        )\n64\t        yield session\n65\t\n66\t\n67\tdef _set_local_statement():\n68\t    \"\"\"Build the `SET LOCAL` statement for the current-tenant RLS setting.\n69\t\n70\t    A separate function keeps the (slightly unusual) `set_config` call —\n71\t    `SET LOCAL` does not accept a bound parameter directly in all drivers —\n72\t    isolated and documented in one place.\n73\t    \"\"\"\n74\t    from sqlalchemy import text\n75\t\n76\t    return text(\"SELECT set_config('app.current_api_key_id', :api_key_id, true)\")\n77\t\n78\t\n79\tasync def dispose_engine() -> None:\n80\t    \"\"\"Dispose of the engine's connection pool (called from lifespan shutdown).\"\"\"\n81\t    global _engine, _session_factory\n82\t    if _engine is not None:\n83\t        await _engine.dispose()\n84\t    _engine = None\n85\t    _session_factory = None\n86\t\n87\t\n88\tasync def check_database_ready() -> bool:\n89\t    \"\"\"Run a fast `SELECT 1` to back the `/health/ready` readiness probe.\"\"\"\n90\t    from sqlalchemy import text\n91\t\n92\t    try:\n93\t        async with get_engine().connect() as connection:\n94\t            await connection.execute(text(\"SELECT 1\"))\n95\t        return True\n96\t    except Exception:  # noqa: BLE001 - readiness must never raise, only report False\n97\t        return False\n98\t"}]},"uuid":"4a0a8c7f-4016-494e-b169-2e84891e7b07","timestamp":"2026-07-08T18:03:28.017Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"5a3e3972-d9bc-4018-a3e4-f074b1c50be3","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"4a0a8c7f-4016-494e-b169-2e84891e7b07","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa3971c3406bc34d2","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccq2k4XHnYYTrDHRLdpCJ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01NEJ3DpqpwHryLPjjk6fmcU","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\main.py"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8028,"cache_read_input_tokens":59514,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":8028,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":7,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccq2k3Q59GfUYMeXzRgEK","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"a7176586-68e0-4078-ad25-d2a02a835f8b","timestamp":"2026-07-08T18:03:28.715Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"a7176586-68e0-4078-ad25-d2a02a835f8b","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"eca00838-5098-4dde-983a-34e68a423bb3","agentId":"aa3971c3406bc34d2","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NEJ3DpqpwHryLPjjk6fmcU","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t\"\"\"Application entry point: constructs the FastAPI app, registers the\n2\tmiddleware stack in the order `api-edge-conventions` requires, mounts the\n3\trouters, and wires the lifespan startup/shutdown hooks.\n4\t\n5\tDeliberately defers every *connecting* dependency (DB pool, Redis client) to\n6\tfirst use rather than import time, so `python -c \"import src.main\"` succeeds\n7\twith no PostgreSQL or Redis running — the smoke check's build-fallback mode\n8\tdepends on this. OTel/Sentry instrumentation is wired during app construction\n9\tinstead of inside the lifespan startup hook: Starlette forbids registering\n10\tASGI middleware (which `FastAPIInstrumentor` does) once the app has started\n11\tserving, and neither call performs a blocking network operation at\n12\tconfiguration time — exporting is async/background and a no-op when\n13\tunconfigured (`src/observability/otel.py`, `src/observability/sentry.py`).\n14\t\"\"\"\n15\t\n16\tfrom collections.abc import AsyncIterator\n17\tfrom contextlib import asynccontextmanager\n18\t\n19\tfrom fastapi import FastAPI\n20\t\n21\tfrom src.api.errors import register_error_handlers\n22\tfrom src.api.middleware import (\n23\t    BodySizeLimitMiddleware,\n24\t    SecurityHeadersMiddleware,\n25\t    Tier1EdgeThrottleMiddleware,\n26\t    configure_cors,\n27\t)\n28\tfrom src.api.routes.events import router as events_router\n29\tfrom src.api.routes.health import router as health_router\n30\tfrom src.api.routes.usage import router as usage_router\n31\tfrom src.config.settings import get_settings\n32\tfrom src.db.session import dispose_engine\n33\tfrom src.logging import get_logger\n34\tfrom src.logging.middleware import RequestContextMiddleware\n35\tfrom src.observability.otel import configure_otel\n36\tfrom src.observability.sentry import configure_sentry\n37\t\n38\tlogger = get_logger(service=\"meterly\")\n39\t\n40\t\n41\t@asynccontextmanager\n42\tasync def lifespan(app: FastAPI) -> AsyncIterator[None]:\n43\t    \"\"\"Startup: log readiness (DB/Redis pools are created lazily on first use,\n44\t    not here, so a slow/unreachable dependency at boot never blocks the\n45\t    process from becoming live). Shutdown: drain and close pools.\n46\t    \"\"\"\n47\t    settings = get_settings()\n48\t    logger.info(\"app.startup\", environment=settings.environment, release=settings.release_sha)\n49\t\n50\t    yield\n51\t\n52\t    logger.info(\"app.shutdown\")\n53\t    await dispose_engine()\n54\t    from src.auth.rate_limit import dispose_redis_client\n55\t\n56\t    await dispose_redis_client()\n57\t\n58\t\n59\tdef create_app() -> FastAPI:\n60\t    \"\"\"Build and configure the FastAPI application (the single app-construction\n61\t    entry point — nothing outside this function registers middleware or routes).\"\"\"\n62\t    settings = get_settings()\n63\t\n64\t    app = FastAPI(\n65\t        title=\"Meterly\",\n66\t        version=\"1.0.0\",\n67\t        lifespan=lifespan,\n68\t        docs_url=\"/docs\" if settings.enable_docs else None,\n69\t        redoc_url=\"/redoc\" if settings.enable_docs else None,\n70\t    )\n71\t\n72\t    # Middleware is applied in reverse-registration order by Starlette (the\n73\t    # last `add_middleware` call becomes the outermost layer), so this list\n74\t    # is written outermost-to-innermost per api-edge-conventions and then\n75\t    # reversed at registration to preserve that intent.\n76\t    app.add_middleware(Tier1EdgeThrottleMiddleware, capacity=settings.tier1_rate_limit_burst, refill_rate_per_second=settings.tier1_rate_limit_per_second)\n77\t    app.add_middleware(BodySizeLimitMiddleware, max_body_size_bytes=settings.max_body_size_bytes)\n78\t    configure_cors(app, settings)\n79\t    app.add_middleware(SecurityHeadersMiddleware)\n80\t    app.add_middleware(RequestContextMiddleware)\n81\t\n82\t    register_error_handlers(app)\n83\t\n84\t    app.include_router(health_router)\n85\t    app.include_router(events_router)\n86\t    app.include_router(usage_router)\n87\t\n88\t    # Must run after routes are mounted (FastAPIInstrumentor introspects them)\n89\t    # and before the app starts serving (it registers ASGI middleware, which\n90\t    # Starlette forbids once serving has begun) — so construction time, not\n91\t    # the lifespan hook, is the correct place for this.\n92\t    configure_sentry(settings)\n93\t    configure_otel(app, settings)\n94\t\n95\t    return app\n96\t\n97\t\n98\tapp = create_app()\n99\t"}]},"uuid":"087ed57d-8609-4ddc-b0d6-c26aeb9c248d","timestamp":"2026-07-08T18:03:28.760Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"a7176586-68e0-4078-ad25-d2a02a835f8b","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"087ed57d-8609-4ddc-b0d6-c26aeb9c248d","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa3971c3406bc34d2","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccq2k4XHnYYTrDHRLdpCJ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_013EJ3mZeaK12b96Ehpy1pzP","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\api\\middleware.py"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8028,"cache_read_input_tokens":59514,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":8028,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":7,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccq2k3Q59GfUYMeXzRgEK","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"6b3b28d0-67e3-4420-b940-c30f8f8ca2f8","timestamp":"2026-07-08T18:03:29.073Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"6b3b28d0-67e3-4420-b940-c30f8f8ca2f8","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"eca00838-5098-4dde-983a-34e68a423bb3","agentId":"aa3971c3406bc34d2","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013EJ3mZeaK12b96Ehpy1pzP","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t\"\"\"Centralized edge middleware — security headers, CORS, the body-size guard,\n2\tand the Tier-1 (pre-auth, IP+route-keyed) throttle.\n3\t\n4\tRegistered once at app construction (`src/main.py`) in the order\n5\t`api-edge-conventions` specifies: request-id/trace, security headers, CORS,\n6\tbody-size guard, Tier-1 throttle, auth guard, Tier-2 throttle, handler. No\n7\troute re-declares any of this — a new endpoint inherits it by being mounted\n8\ton the app.\n9\t\"\"\"\n10\t\n11\tfrom collections.abc import Awaitable, Callable\n12\t\n13\tfrom fastapi import FastAPI, status\n14\tfrom fastapi.middleware.cors import CORSMiddleware\n15\tfrom starlette.middleware.base import BaseHTTPMiddleware\n16\tfrom starlette.requests import Request\n17\tfrom starlette.responses import JSONResponse, Response\n18\t\n19\tfrom src.auth.rate_limit import get_tier1_limiter\n20\tfrom src.config.settings import Settings\n21\tfrom src.logging import get_logger\n22\t\n23\tlogger = get_logger(service=\"meterly\")\n24\t\n25\t_SECURITY_HEADERS = {\n26\t    \"Strict-Transport-Security\": \"max-age=63072000; includeSubDomains\",\n27\t    \"X-Content-Type-Options\": \"nosniff\",\n28\t    \"Content-Security-Policy\": \"default-src 'none'\",\n29\t    \"X-Frame-Options\": \"DENY\",\n30\t    \"Referrer-Policy\": \"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\",\n31\t    \"Permissions-Policy\": \"geolocation=(), camera=(), microphone=()\",\n32\t}\n33\t\n34\t\n35\tclass SecurityHeadersMiddleware(BaseHTTPMiddleware):\n36\t    \"\"\"Sets a fixed set of security headers on every response, including error responses.\"\"\"\n37\t\n38\t    async def dispatch(\n39\t        self, request: Request, call_next: Callable[[Request], Awaitable[Response]]\n40\t    ) -> Response:\n41\t        \"\"\"Run the request, then stamp the security header set onto the response.\"\"\"\n42\t        response = await call_next(request)\n43\t        for header_name, header_value in _SECURITY_HEADERS.items():\n44\t            response.headers[header_name] = header_value\n45\t        if request.url.path.startswith(\"/v1/usage\"):\n46\t            # Usage totals are billing-adjacent personal-scoped data — never cache\n47\t            # them client-side or in an intermediary (ASVS 14.3.2).\n48\t            response.headers[\"Cache-Control\"] = \"no-store\"\n49\t        return response\n50\t\n51\t\n52\tclass BodySizeLimitMiddleware(BaseHTTPMiddleware):\n53\t    \"\"\"Rejects a request whose `Content-Length` exceeds the configured cap with 413.\n54\t\n55\t    These payloads are tiny by design (a handful of scalar fields); an\n56\t    unbounded body is a cheap denial-of-service vector worth rejecting before\n57\t    it reaches any parsing.\n58\t    \"\"\"\n59\t\n60\t    def __init__(self, app: FastAPI, *, max_body_size_bytes: int) -> None:\n61\t        super().__init__(app)\n62\t        self._max_body_size_bytes = max_body_size_bytes\n63\t\n64\t    async def dispatch(\n65\t        self, request: Request, call_next: Callable[[Request], Awaitable[Response]]\n66\t    ) -> Response:\n67\t        \"\"\"Check `Content-Length` before invoking the rest of the stack.\"\"\"\n68\t        content_length = request.headers.get(\"content-length\")\n69\t        if content_length is not None:\n70\t            try:\n71\t                if int(content_length) > self._max_body_size_bytes:\n72\t                    return JSONResponse(\n73\t                        status_code=status.HTTP_413_REQUEST_ENTITY_TOO_LARGE,\n74\t                        content={\n75\t                            \"error\": {\n76\t                                \"code\": \"payload_too_large\",\n77\t                                \"message\": \"request body exceeds the maximum allowed size\",\n78\t                                \"requestId\": getattr(request.state, \"request_id\", \"unknown\"),\n79\t                            }\n80\t                        },\n81\t                    )\n82\t            except ValueError:\n83\t                pass  # malformed Content-Length falls through to normal request handling/validation\n84\t        return await call_next(request)\n85\t\n86\t\n87\t# Paths exempt from the Tier-1 Redis throttle: the liveness probe must return\n88\t# 200 with *zero* dependencies (no DB, no Redis) — it is the smoke check's and\n89\t# the build-fallback's only signal, and gating it on Redis would make a cache\n90\t# outage look like a total application outage (plan §\"health split\").\n91\t_TIER1_EXEMPT_PATHS = frozenset({\"/health\"})\n92\t\n93\t\n94\tclass Tier1EdgeThrottleMiddleware(BaseHTTPMiddleware):\n95\t    \"\"\"Pre-auth, IP+route-keyed Redis token bucket — sheds an anonymous flood\n96\t    before the request can spend an Argon2id verification (mitigates D1/D3).\n97\t    \"\"\"\n98\t\n99\t    def __init__(self, app: FastAPI, *, capacity: int, refill_rate_per_second: float) -> None:\n100\t        super().__init__(app)\n101\t        self._capacity = capacity\n102\t        self._refill_rate_per_second = refill_rate_per_second\n103\t\n104\t    async def dispatch(\n105\t        self, request: Request, call_next: Callable[[Request], Awaitable[Response]]\n106\t    ) -> Response:\n107\t        \"\"\"Consume one token from the `client_ip:route` bucket before proceeding.\n108\t\n109\t        Fails **open** (allows the request, logs a warning) on a Redis\n110\t        connection error rather than 500ing every request — an unreachable\n111\t        cache degrading to \"temporarily unlimited\" is preferable to a full\n112\t        outage of the ingest path; Tier-2's per-key bucket and the underlying\n113\t        DB constraints remain the durable protections either way.\n114\t        \"\"\"\n115\t        if request.url.path in _TIER1_EXEMPT_PATHS:\n116\t            return await call_next(request)\n117\t\n118\t        client_ip = request.client.host if request.client else \"unknown\"\n119\t        bucket_identity = f\"{client_ip}:{request.url.path}\"\n120\t        try:\n121\t            decision = await get_tier1_limiter().check(\n122\t                bucket_identity,\n123\t                capacity=self._capacity,\n124\t                refill_rate_per_second=self._refill_rate_per_second,\n125\t            )\n126\t        except Exception:  # noqa: BLE001 - a Redis outage must not take down the whole API\n127\t            logger.warning(\"ratelimit.backend_unavailable\", endpoint=request.url.path, tier=\"tier1\")\n128\t            return await call_next(request)\n129\t\n130\t        if not decision.allowed:\n131\t            logger.warning(\n132\t                \"ratelimit.exceeded\",\n133\t                userId=None,\n134\t                action=\"deny\",\n135\t                endpoint=request.url.path,\n136\t                reason=\"tier1_bucket_exhausted\",\n137\t            )\n138\t            return JSONResponse(\n139\t                status_code=status.HTTP_429_TOO_MANY_REQUESTS,\n140\t                content={\n141\t                    \"error\": {\n142\t                        \"code\": \"rate_limited\",\n143\t                        \"message\": \"too many requests\",\n144\t                        \"requestId\": getattr(request.state, \"request_id\", \"unknown\"),\n145\t                    }\n146\t                },\n147\t                headers={\"Retry-After\": str(max(1, int(decision.retry_after_seconds) or 1))},\n148\t            )\n149\t        return await call_next(request)\n150\t\n151\t\n152\tdef configure_cors(app: FastAPI, settings: Settings) -> None:\n153\t    \"\"\"Register the CORS middleware with an explicit origin allowlist from config.\n154\t\n155\t    Defaults to an empty allowlist (this is a server-to-server API, not a\n156\t    browser client) rather than `*` — `api-edge-conventions` forbids\n157\t    reflecting an arbitrary origin.\n158\t    \"\"\"\n159\t    app.add_middleware(\n160\t        CORSMiddleware,\n161\t        allow_origins=list(settings.cors_allowed_origins),\n162\t        allow_credentials=False,\n163\t        allow_methods=[\"GET\", \"POST\"],\n164\t        allow_headers=[\"Authorization\", \"Content-Type\", \"Idempotency-Key\"],\n165\t    )\n166\t"}]},"uuid":"fb2955f9-477f-4d90-be63-806a3ef13ee8","timestamp":"2026-07-08T18:03:29.113Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"6b3b28d0-67e3-4420-b940-c30f8f8ca2f8","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"fb2955f9-477f-4d90-be63-806a3ef13ee8","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa3971c3406bc34d2","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccq2k4XHnYYTrDHRLdpCJ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_019HmpES7qrape2YnsQqZqGB","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\auth\\__init__.py"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8028,"cache_read_input_tokens":59514,"output_tokens":413,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":8028},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":413,"cache_read_input_tokens":59514,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8028,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":8028,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccq2k3Q59GfUYMeXzRgEK","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"4a618c12-8737-407c-a7e8-56b5ff01630e","timestamp":"2026-07-08T18:03:29.332Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"4a618c12-8737-407c-a7e8-56b5ff01630e","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"eca00838-5098-4dde-983a-34e68a423bb3","agentId":"aa3971c3406bc34d2","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019HmpES7qrape2YnsQqZqGB","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t\"\"\"Auth facade — `require_api_key` is the only guard route handlers depend on.\n2\t\n3\tResolves the exact tension the plan calls out: Argon2id is intentionally slow\n4\t(tens of ms), so running it on every request at the target 500 req/s would\n5\tblow the ingest p95 budget. An in-process verification cache, keyed by the\n6\ttoken's public `key_id` and guarded by a constant-time digest comparison\n7\t(ASVS 11.2.4 — in-scope L3), lets a repeat caller on the same task skip the\n8\tArgon2id verify after the first request while the durable at-rest store stays\n9\tArgon2id-only. See the plan's \"Argon2id-vs-p95 tension\" section for the full\n10\ttradeoff writeup, including the accepted ~5 min revocation-latency risk (Q4).\n11\t\"\"\"\n12\t\n13\timport time\n14\tfrom dataclasses import dataclass\n15\t\n16\tfrom fastapi import Depends, HTTPException, Request, status\n17\t\n18\tfrom src.auth.api_key import AuthenticatedPrincipal, parse_split_token, verify_api_key\n19\tfrom src.config.settings import get_settings\n20\tfrom src.crypto import constant_time_equals, sha256_digest\n21\tfrom src.db.session import get_engine\n22\tfrom src.logging import get_logger\n23\t\n24\tlogger = get_logger(service=\"meterly\")\n25\t\n26\t_BEARER_PREFIX = \"Bearer \"\n27\t\n28\t\n29\t@dataclass\n30\tclass _CachedVerification:\n31\t    \"\"\"An in-process cache entry: the digest of the secret that was last\n32\t    verified for this `key_id`, and the resolved principal.\"\"\"\n33\t\n34\t    secret_digest: str\n35\t    principal: AuthenticatedPrincipal\n36\t    cached_at: float\n37\t\n38\t\n39\tclass ApiKeyVerificationCache:\n40\t    \"\"\"Per-process cache mapping a token's public `key_id` to its last-verified\n41\t    secret digest and resolved principal, with a TTL.\n42\t\n43\t    Keyed on the *public* `key_id` (not a secret) so the cache lookup itself\n44\t    leaks nothing; the constant-time digest comparison is what actually\n45\t    authorizes a cache hit.\n46\t    \"\"\"\n47\t\n48\t    def __init__(self, ttl_seconds: int) -> None:\n49\t        self._ttl_seconds = ttl_seconds\n50\t        self._entries: dict[str, _CachedVerification] = {}\n51\t\n52\t    def get(self, key_id: str, secret_digest: str) -> AuthenticatedPrincipal | None:\n53\t        \"\"\"Return the cached principal if `key_id` has a fresh, matching entry.\"\"\"\n54\t        entry = self._entries.get(key_id)\n55\t        if entry is None:\n56\t            return None\n57\t        if (time.monotonic() - entry.cached_at) > self._ttl_seconds:\n58\t            del self._entries[key_id]\n59\t            return None\n60\t        if not constant_time_equals(secret_digest, entry.secret_digest):\n61\t            return None\n62\t        return entry.principal\n63\t\n64\t    def put(self, key_id: str, secret_digest: str, principal: AuthenticatedPrincipal) -> None:\n65\t        \"\"\"Cache a freshly Argon2id-verified principal for `key_id`.\"\"\"\n66\t        self._entries[key_id] = _CachedVerification(\n67\t            secret_digest=secret_digest, principal=principal, cached_at=time.monotonic()\n68\t        )\n69\t\n70\t    def invalidate(self, key_id: str) -> None:\n71\t        \"\"\"Drop a cached entry (used by tests and any future revocation channel).\"\"\"\n72\t        self._entries.pop(key_id, None)\n73\t\n74\t\n75\t_verification_cache: ApiKeyVerificationCache | None = None\n76\t\n77\t\n78\tdef _get_verification_cache() -> ApiKeyVerificationCache:\n79\t    \"\"\"Return the process-wide verification cache, created on first use.\"\"\"\n80\t    global _verification_cache\n81\t    if _verification_cache is None:\n82\t        _verification_cache = ApiKeyVerificationCache(get_settings().api_key_cache_ttl_seconds)\n83\t    return _verification_cache\n84\t\n85\t\n86\tdef _extract_bearer_token(request: Request) -> str | None:\n87\t    \"\"\"Pull the raw bearer token out of the `Authorization` header, if present and well-formed.\"\"\"\n88\t    header_value = request.headers.get(\"authorization\")\n89\t    if not header_value or not header_value.startswith(_BEARER_PREFIX):\n90\t        return None\n91\t    return header_value[len(_BEARER_PREFIX) :]\n92\t\n93\t\n94\tasync def require_api_key(request: Request) -> AuthenticatedPrincipal:\n95\t    \"\"\"FastAPI dependency: authenticate the request's API key.\n96\t\n97\t    Cache hit path: constant-time digest compare only (no Argon2id). Cache\n98\t    miss: split-token parse + DB lookup + Argon2id verify, then populate the\n99\t    cache. Any failure raises 401 — malformed header, unknown/revoked key, and\n100\t    a wrong secret are all indistinguishable to the caller.\n101\t    \"\"\"\n102\t    presented_key = _extract_bearer_token(request)\n103\t    if presented_key is None:\n104\t        logger.warning(\"apikey.auth\", userId=None, action=\"deny\", reason=\"missing_or_malformed_header\")\n105\t        raise HTTPException(status_code=status.HTTP_401_UNAUTHORIZED, detail=\"authentication required\")\n106\t\n107\t    parsed = parse_split_token(presented_key)\n108\t    if parsed is None:\n109\t        logger.warning(\"apikey.auth\", userId=None, action=\"deny\", reason=\"malformed_token\")\n110\t        raise HTTPException(status_code=status.HTTP_401_UNAUTHORIZED, detail=\"invalid API key\")\n111\t\n112\t    secret_digest = sha256_digest(presented_key)\n113\t    cache = _get_verification_cache()\n114\t    cached_principal = cache.get(parsed.key_id, secret_digest)\n115\t    if cached_principal is not None:\n116\t        logger.info(\"apikey.auth\", userId=cached_principal.api_key_id, action=\"allow\", reason=\"cache_hit\")\n117\t        return cached_principal\n118\t\n119\t    async with get_engine().connect() as connection:\n120\t        principal = await verify_api_key(connection, presented_key)\n121\t\n122\t    if principal is None:\n123\t        logger.warning(\"apikey.auth\", userId=None, action=\"deny\", reason=\"verification_failed\")\n124\t        raise HTTPException(status_code=status.HTTP_401_UNAUTHORIZED, detail=\"invalid API key\")\n125\t\n126\t    cache.put(parsed.key_id, secret_digest, principal)\n127\t    logger.info(\"apikey.auth\", userId=principal.api_key_id, action=\"allow\", reason=\"verified\")\n128\t    return principal\n129\t\n130\t\n131\tApiKeyPrincipal = Depends(require_api_key)\n132\t"}]},"uuid":"790713c5-978f-4d43-9cf1-7bc7deef9f6c","timestamp":"2026-07-08T18:03:29.382Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"4a618c12-8737-407c-a7e8-56b5ff01630e","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
