{"parentUuid":"cd348aa5-b72a-430d-8dbc-af654d2bbdce","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa3971c3406bc34d2","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccq2nhKfiUnj5gnhoYePN","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_019FRyZGAQiNwDfHiSiVAfQm","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\docs\\system_architecture.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8720,"cache_read_input_tokens":106177,"output_tokens":298,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":8720},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":298,"cache_read_input_tokens":106177,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8720,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":8720,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccq2ng41sYHC9CJX5bHmH","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"ca85f8f5-d8ee-4811-9499-7055c6b45b89","timestamp":"2026-07-08T18:04:05.314Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"ca85f8f5-d8ee-4811-9499-7055c6b45b89","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"eca00838-5098-4dde-983a-34e68a423bb3","agentId":"aa3971c3406bc34d2","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019FRyZGAQiNwDfHiSiVAfQm","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Meterly — system architecture (first feature)\n2\t\n3\t## Overview\n4\t\n5\tMeterly ingests metered usage events and serves aggregated per-customer/metric\n6\tcounters. Two authenticated HTTP endpoints, one PostgreSQL database, one Redis\n7\trate-limit store, running as a Docker container on ECS Fargate behind an ALB.\n8\t\n9\t```\n10\tClient --HTTPS+API key--> ALB --> FastAPI (ECS Fargate, >=2 tasks)\n11\t                                     |-- Tier-1 (IP) / Tier-2 (api_key_id) throttle --> Redis\n12\t                                     |-- bound-parameter SQL, RLS-scoped -------------> RDS PostgreSQL\n13\t                                     |-- DB credential fetch ------------------------> Secrets Manager\n14\t                                     |-- traces/logs/errors -------------------------> CloudWatch/X-Ray/Sentry\n15\t```\n16\t\n17\t## Request flow — `POST /v1/events`\n18\t\n19\t1. Request-id/trace assigned, security headers queued (`src/logging/middleware.py`, `src/api/middleware.py`).\n20\t2. Tier-1 IP+route throttle (Redis token bucket; fails open on a Redis outage).\n21\t3. `require_api_key` — split-token parse, in-process verification-cache check,\n22\t   falling back to a DB lookup + Argon2id verify on a cache miss\n23\t   (`src/auth/__init__.py`, `src/auth/api_key.py`).\n24\t4. Tier-2 per-`api_key_id` throttle (`src/auth/rate_limit.py`).\n25\t5. Pydantic schema validation (`src/api/schemas/events.py`) — anchored\n26\t   allowlists, `extra='forbid'`.\n27\t6. `events_service.create_event` — one transaction:\n28\t   `INSERT ... ON CONFLICT (api_key_id, idempotency_key) DO NOTHING`, and only\n29\t   if a row was inserted, `INSERT ... ON CONFLICT ... DO UPDATE` the\n30\t   `usage_rollup` counter (`src/services/events_service.py`,\n31\t   `src/repositories/events_repo.py`).\n32\t7. Error-envelope boundary catches anything unhandled and returns the generic\n33\t   `{error:{code,message,requestId}}` shape (`src/api/errors.py`).\n34\t\n35\t## Request flow — `GET /v1/usage`\n36\t\n37\tSame auth/throttle/error stack; the service floors `window` to the UTC hour\n38\tand reads a single `usage_rollup` row scoped by the caller's `api_key_id`\n39\t(`src/services/usage_service.py`, `src/repositories/usage_repo.py`). A missing\n40\tbucket returns zeros with 200, never 404.\n41\t\n42\t## Data model\n43\t\n44\t- `api_keys` — the tenant/credential table (migration 0001). `secret_hash` is\n45\t  Argon2id; `key_id` is the public split-token lookup handle.\n46\t- `events` — append-only ingest log (migration 0001). `UNIQUE (api_key_id,\n47\t  idempotency_key)` is the idempotency guarantee; RLS policy\n48\t  `events_tenant_isolation` is the application-scoping backstop.\n49\t- `usage_rollup` — derived hourly aggregate (migration 0002, expand +\n50\t  backfill from `events`). Composite PK `(api_key_id, customer_id, metric,\n51\t  window_start)`; RLS policy `usage_rollup_tenant_isolation`.\n52\t\n53\t## Auth\n54\t\n55\tSplit-token API keys (`mtr_live_<key_id>_<secret>`), Argon2id-hashed at rest.\n56\tAn in-process, TTL-bounded verification cache (keyed on the public `key_id`,\n57\tguarded by a constant-time digest comparison) avoids paying the Argon2id cost\n58\ton every request while the durable store stays Argon2id-only. See\n59\t`src/auth/__init__.py` for the full tradeoff writeup and\n60\t`scripts/seed_api_key.py` for the only key-provisioning path (no HTTP\n61\tendpoint in this build's scope).\n62\t\n63\t## Rate limiting\n64\t\n65\tTwo Redis token-bucket tiers (`src/auth/rate_limit.py`): Tier-1 pre-auth,\n66\tkeyed on IP+route; Tier-2 post-auth, keyed on the authenticated\n67\t`api_key_id`. Both fail open (log a warning, allow the request) on a Redis\n68\tconnection error rather than failing every request — an availability\n69\ttradeoff recorded in `.pipeline/surface-delta.md`.\n70\t\n71\t## Observability\n72\t\n73\tStructured JSON logs (structlog) to stdout -> CloudWatch, with a centralized\n74\tredaction processor (`src/logging/__init__.py`). OTel traces -> ADOT sidecar\n75\t-> X-Ray; Sentry for release-tagged error tracking with a `before_send`\n76\tPII/secret scrubber (`src/observability/`). SLO burn-rate alarms and the\n77\tminimum-three canary alarms are declared in `infra/modules/observability`.\n78\t\n79\t## Infrastructure\n80\t\n81\tTerraform under `infra/`: `modules/{network,compute,data,observability,edge}`\n82\thold the real resources; `envs/{staging,prod}/main.tf` are the two\n83\tself-contained deploy roots (own provider + backend, since Terraform only\n84\tpermits a backend configuration in a root module) that instantiate the same\n85\tmodules at different scale. See each module's file header comments for the\n86\tspecific resources and the security-baseline items they satisfy\n87\t(encryption at rest, private subnets, least-privilege IAM, no `BYPASSRLS`).\n88\t\n89\t## Known deviations / accepted risks\n90\t\n91\tSee `.pipeline/surface-delta.md` for the rate-limit fail-open behavior and the\n92\tOTel/Sentry wiring-at-construction-time change vs. the plan's original\n93\tlifespan-hook placement. See `plan.md`'s \"Open questions\" section for the\n94\taccepted risks around key-revocation latency, `api_key_id`-as-tenant-scope,\n95\tand the Postgres app-role bootstrap's CI-network-reachability prerequisite.\n96\t"}]},"uuid":"452b206e-2301-4a8a-99cc-853045beee01","timestamp":"2026-07-08T18:04:05.345Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"ca85f8f5-d8ee-4811-9499-7055c6b45b89","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
