{"parentUuid":"8d3815b9-8dba-43a3-b7ba-73d65cf418af","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa3971c3406bc34d2","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcqBgjn8Yd3SZGXcY2Geh","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Y9LPCVCmwgFc2pqfV9EE9a","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\api\\README.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":502,"cache_read_input_tokens":258526,"output_tokens":126,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":502},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":126,"cache_read_input_tokens":258526,"cache_creation_input_tokens":502,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":502,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcqBggeMyyzrTsZrwxMar","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"57bf29ea-25f0-41bb-9142-7df4ea172841","timestamp":"2026-07-08T20:00:44.107Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"57bf29ea-25f0-41bb-9142-7df4ea172841","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"eca00838-5098-4dde-983a-34e68a423bb3","agentId":"aa3971c3406bc34d2","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Y9LPCVCmwgFc2pqfV9EE9a","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# src/api/\n2\t\n3\t## Purpose\n4\t\n5\tHTTP API layer: FastAPI route handlers, request/response schemas (Pydantic v2), error envelope boundary, and edge-concern middleware (request ID, security headers, CORS, body-size guards).\n6\t\n7\t## Modules\n8\t\n9\t| File / Module | Responsibility |\n10\t|---|---|\n11\t| `routes/events.py` | `POST /v1/events` handler; calls `events_service.create_event`. |\n12\t| `routes/usage.py` | `GET /v1/usage` handler; calls `usage_service.read_usage`. |\n13\t| `routes/health.py` | `GET /health` (liveness, no dependencies) and `GET /health/ready` (readiness, DB + migration check). |\n14\t| `schemas/events.py` | Pydantic models for POST /v1/events request and response; `extra='forbid'` contract enforcement. |\n15\t| `schemas/usage.py` | Pydantic models for GET /v1/usage request (query parameters) and response. |\n16\t| `middleware.py` | Request-ID / trace-ID assignment, security headers (HSTS, CSP, X-Frame-Options), CORS. |\n17\t| `errors.py` | Error-envelope boundary: catches all unhandled exceptions and returns `{error:{code,message,requestId}}` with no stack/secret leakage. |\n18\t\n19\t## Relationships\n20\t\n21\t**Public surface:**\n22\t- Imported by `src/main.py` to register routes with FastAPI.\n23\t- Exposes `get_app()` function which returns the fully-configured FastAPI instance.\n24\t\n25\t**Dependencies:**\n26\t- `middleware.py` and `errors.py` are registered once at app construction (middleware stack + exception handler).\n27\t- Each route handler uses `require_api_key` guard from `src/auth` to enforce authentication.\n28\t- Route handlers call `src/services.{events_service, usage_service}` to execute business logic.\n29\t- Schemas validate request bodies/parameters; malformed input raises Pydantic `ValidationError` → 422.\n30\t- Middleware and error boundary run for all routes, ensuring every response has proper headers and envelope shape.\n31\t\n32\t**Middleware ordering (in `main.py`):**\n33\t1. Request-ID / trace (outermost) — sets correlation context for all downstream logging.\n34\t2. Security headers — applied to every response.\n35\t3. CORS — explicit allowlist from config.\n36\t4. Body-size guard — reject Content-Length > 8 KiB.\n37\t5. Tier-1 edge throttle (pre-auth) — IP+route keyed.\n38\t6. `require_api_key` guard — auth.\n39\t7. Tier-2 per-key throttle (post-auth) — api_key_id keyed.\n40\t8. Route handler (innermost) — wrapped by error-envelope boundary.\n41\t\n42\t## Notes\n43\t\n44\t**Contract enforcement:**\n45\t- Request bodies are validated against Pydantic schemas; `extra='forbid'` rejects unknown fields.\n46\t- All string fields are bounded length (e.g., `customer_id` ≤128, `metric` ≤64).\n47\t- `quantity` is a decimal > 0 (no zero or negative); `idempotency_key` is alphanumeric + underscore/dash.\n48\t- GET `/v1/usage` requires a timezone-aware ISO-8601 `window` parameter within 90 days past to 1 hour future (naive datetimes rejected).\n49\t\n50\t**Error handling:**\n51\t- Authentication failures (missing/invalid key) → 401/403 before handlers run.\n52\t- Rate-limit exceeded (Tier-1 or Tier-2) → 429 + Retry-After header.\n53\t- Schema validation failure → 422 with Pydantic error detail.\n54\t- Database errors (constraint violation, connection drop) → caught by error envelope → 500 (generic message, safe).\n55\t- Any unhandled exception → error envelope → 500, safe, no leak.\n56\t\n57\t**Security headers (all responses):**\n58\t- `Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains` (production only; localhost omitted).\n59\t- `X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff` — disable MIME sniffing.\n60\t- `X-Frame-Options: DENY` — no embedding in iframes.\n61\t- `Cache-Control: no-store, no-cache, must-revalidate, max-age=0` (API, not HTML).\n62\t"}]},"uuid":"b473f593-784b-4af7-aa3b-75ff691069f9","timestamp":"2026-07-08T20:00:44.136Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"57bf29ea-25f0-41bb-9142-7df4ea172841","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"b473f593-784b-4af7-aa3b-75ff691069f9","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa3971c3406bc34d2","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcqBh21SY8y1yQE2dbRux","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Q11Dt1hjQoF1wLa9ix85m2","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\api\\README.md","old_string":"| `routes/events.py` | `POST /v1/events` handler; calls `events_service.create_event`. |\n| `routes/usage.py` | `GET /v1/usage` handler; calls `usage_service.read_usage`. |\n| `routes/health.py` | `GET /health` (liveness, no dependencies) and `GET /health/ready` (readiness, DB + migration check). |\n| `schemas/events.py` | Pydantic models for POST /v1/events request and response; `extra='forbid'` contract enforcement. |\n| `schemas/usage.py` | Pydantic models for GET /v1/usage request (query parameters) and response. |\n| `middleware.py` | Request-ID / trace-ID assignment, security headers (HSTS, CSP, X-Frame-Options), CORS. |\n| `errors.py` | Error-envelope boundary: catches all unhandled exceptions and returns `{error:{code,message,requestId}}` with no stack/secret leakage. |","new_string":"| `routes/events.py` | `POST /v1/events` handler; calls `events_service.create_event`. |\n| `routes/usage.py` | `GET /v1/usage` handler; calls `usage_service.read_usage`. |\n| `routes/quotas.py` | `PUT /v1/quotas` handler; composes auth -> Tier-2 throttle -> an `admin`-scope gate (403 `forbidden` otherwise) -> `quota_service.upsert_tenant_quota`. |\n| `routes/health.py` | `GET /health` (liveness, no dependencies) and `GET /health/ready` (readiness, DB + migration check). |\n| `schemas/events.py` | Pydantic models for POST /v1/events request and response; `extra='forbid'` contract enforcement. |\n| `schemas/usage.py` | Pydantic models for GET /v1/usage request (query parameters) and response. |\n| `schemas/quotas.py` | Pydantic models for PUT /v1/quotas request (`customer_id`, `metric`, `limit_per_window`, `extra='forbid'`) and response (echo shape). |\n| `middleware.py` | Request-ID / trace-ID assignment, security headers (HSTS, CSP, X-Frame-Options), CORS (allows GET/POST/PUT). |\n| `errors.py` | Error-envelope boundary: catches all unhandled exceptions and returns `{error:{code,message,requestId}}` with no stack/secret leakage. `AppError` lets a raised exception carry an explicit `app_code` (e.g. `quota_exceeded`) that overrides the default status->code map — needed because 429 is shared by two distinct codes (`rate_limited` vs `quota_exceeded`). |"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1664,"cache_read_input_tokens":259028,"output_tokens":1042,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1664},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":1042,"cache_read_input_tokens":259028,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1664,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1664,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcqBgz1PmmSWNEBhVjMqr","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"1edbb4ea-d906-4714-915e-63126d954bc3","timestamp":"2026-07-08T20:00:55.186Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
