{"parentUuid":"1d3a4ed1-3d1d-4227-909c-2ebfc75a78d1","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa3971c3406bc34d2","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcqBincbE7oz3EbbB8CTm","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Hjjo3eLtyJJvA6Q9xwiKBt","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\services\\README.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1177,"cache_read_input_tokens":261832,"output_tokens":102,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1177},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":102,"cache_read_input_tokens":261832,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1177,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1177,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcqBikbJTYECjbMw195XZ","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"7a1eced2-b1de-488d-b7ab-1a2388edead5","timestamp":"2026-07-08T20:01:12.081Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"7a1eced2-b1de-488d-b7ab-1a2388edead5","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"eca00838-5098-4dde-983a-34e68a423bb3","agentId":"aa3971c3406bc34d2","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Hjjo3eLtyJJvA6Q9xwiKBt","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# src/services/\n2\t\n3\t## Purpose\n4\t\n5\tBusiness logic layer: event ingestion (with idempotency and counter atomicity), usage aggregation, and time-window calculations. Orchestrates repositories and enforces domain invariants.\n6\t\n7\t## Modules\n8\t\n9\t| File / Module | Responsibility |\n10\t|---|---|\n11\t| `events_service.py` | `create_event(api_key_id, customer_id, metric, quantity, idempotency_key)` — inserts an event + increments the hourly counter in one transaction; idempotent on `idempotency_key`. Returns the created/replayed event. |\n12\t| `usage_service.py` | `read_usage(api_key_id, customer_id, metric, window)` — reads the aggregated counter for a time bucket; returns zeros if the bucket is empty (never 404). |\n13\t| `time_windows.py` | `window_start_utc(ts: datetime)` — floors a timezone-aware timestamp to the hour (UTC); used by both services. |\n14\t\n15\t## Relationships\n16\t\n17\t**Public surface:**\n18\t- Imported by `src/api.routes.{events, usage}` to execute the core business operations.\n19\t\n20\t**Dependencies:**\n21\t- `events_service` imports `src/repositories.{events_repo, usage_repo}` to insert the event and upsert the counter.\n22\t- `usage_service` imports `src/repositories.usage_repo` to read the rollup.\n23\t- Both services receive an authenticated `api_key_id` from the route handler (set by `require_api_key` guard).\n24\t- `time_windows` is imported by `events_service` and `usage_service` to floor timestamps.\n25\t\n26\t**Transaction boundary:**\n27\t- `create_event` wraps both the event insert and the rollup upsert in one PostgreSQL transaction (via `src/db/session_context`).\n28\t- This atomicity ensures that if the insert wins (no existing `idempotency_key`), the counter increments exactly once.\n29\t- If the insert loses (duplicate key), neither the counter nor any side effect happens — a no-op.\n30\t\n31\t## Notes\n32\t\n33\t**Idempotency guarantee:**\n34\t- The unique constraint `UNIQUE (api_key_id, idempotency_key)` on the `events` table is the source of truth.\n35\t- Exactly one of N concurrent identical requests will succeed; the rest get a duplicate-key constraint violation (caught, no exception raised to handler) and fall through to a replay branch.\n36\t- The replay branch reads the original event from the table and returns it, so the caller sees a consistent result across retries.\n37\t- Recorded in the plan as the **AC-CONCURRENCY** mechanism: 50 concurrent same-key POSTs produce exactly one row and 49 get the replay response (200 vs. 201).\n38\t\n39\t**Counter atomicity:**\n40\t- The event insert and the rollup upsert are in one transaction, so both commit or both roll back.\n41\t- This means a counter never gets incremented without the event being persisted (no partial writes).\n42\t- Also means a duplicate event never increments the counter (no double-counting).\n43\t- The counter uses `INSERT ... ON CONFLICT ... DO UPDATE` with `total_quantity + EXCLUDED.total_quantity` to handle the increment (PostgreSQL's row-level conflict resolution, atomic at the SQL level).\n44\t\n45\t**Time-window semantics:**\n46\t- A timestamp is floored to its hour (UTC) to get the `window_start`. E.g., `2026-07-06T14:35:42Z` → `2026-07-06T14:00:00Z`.\n47\t- The floor is done explicitly in Python (`ts.replace(minute=0, second=0, microsecond=0)`) rather than in the database, because PostgreSQL's `date_trunc('hour', ts)` is STABLE (depends on session timezone), not IMMUTABLE, so it cannot be used in a stored generated column.\n48\t- All windows are in UTC; clients must provide timezone-aware ISO-8601 timestamps on GET.\n49\t\n50\t**Scoping by api_key_id:**\n51\t- Both services receive the authenticated `api_key_id` from the route guard (set in `request.state`).\n52\t- Both services pass it to the repository layer, which includes it in the WHERE clause (e.g., `WHERE api_key_id = :auth_key AND customer_id = :customer_id`).\n53\t- This is the primary RLS mechanism; the PostgreSQL RLS policy is the backstop.\n54\t"}]},"uuid":"eaba4c16-9932-42d5-bc28-c2db4ac30b05","timestamp":"2026-07-08T20:01:12.093Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"7a1eced2-b1de-488d-b7ab-1a2388edead5","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"eaba4c16-9932-42d5-bc28-c2db4ac30b05","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa3971c3406bc34d2","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcqBj5d36NkztoVZwrH8F","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01R9orNGrhGW6BZH8BLZTGRV","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\services\\README.md","old_string":"| `events_service.py` | `create_event(api_key_id, customer_id, metric, quantity, idempotency_key)` — inserts an event + increments the hourly counter in one transaction; idempotent on `idempotency_key`. Returns the created/replayed event. |\n| `usage_service.py` | `read_usage(api_key_id, customer_id, metric, window)` — reads the aggregated counter for a time bucket; returns zeros if the bucket is empty (never 404). |\n| `time_windows.py` | `window_start_utc(ts: datetime)` — floors a timezone-aware timestamp to the hour (UTC); used by both services. |","new_string":"| `events_service.py` | `create_event(principal, payload)` — inserts an event, checks the caller's quota (if any) on the winning-insert branch, and increments the hourly counter, all in one transaction; idempotent on `idempotency_key`. Raises `QuotaExceededError` (429 `quota_exceeded`) when `R + Q > L`, which rolls back the event insert. Returns the created/replayed event. |\n| `usage_service.py` | `read_usage(api_key_id, customer_id, metric, window)` — reads the aggregated counter for a time bucket; returns zeros if the bucket is empty (never 404). |\n| `quota_service.py` | `upsert_tenant_quota(principal, payload)` — create-or-replaces the caller's cap for `(customer_id, metric)` in one transaction; maps the repository's insert-vs-replace signal to 201/200 and logs the `quota.upsert` audit event. |\n| `time_windows.py` | `window_start_utc(ts: datetime)` — floors a timezone-aware timestamp to the hour (UTC); used by all three services. |"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1640,"cache_read_input_tokens":263009,"output_tokens":738,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1640},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":738,"cache_read_input_tokens":263009,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1640,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1640,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcqBj3w5vTQb7TYJVELiL","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"06e4d7d1-3ba6-4fb9-af12-8832626e5d23","timestamp":"2026-07-08T20:01:20.880Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"06e4d7d1-3ba6-4fb9-af12-8832626e5d23","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"eca00838-5098-4dde-983a-34e68a423bb3","agentId":"aa3971c3406bc34d2","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01R9orNGrhGW6BZH8BLZTGRV","type":"tool_result","content":"The file C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\services\\README.md has been updated successfully. (file state is current in your context — no need to Read it back)"}]},"uuid":"ccb1b032-22af-403e-b468-147eac3e5e53","timestamp":"2026-07-08T20:01:21.911Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"06e4d7d1-3ba6-4fb9-af12-8832626e5d23","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"ccb1b032-22af-403e-b468-147eac3e5e53","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa3971c3406bc34d2","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcqBjpkMp4SS1fPeCdZQ9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Gcu6wSXtgV8p3xNjAiAT2T","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\services\\README.md","old_string":"**Public surface:**\n- Imported by `src/api.routes.{events, usage}` to execute the core business operations.\n\n**Dependencies:**\n- `events_service` imports `src/repositories.{events_repo, usage_repo}` to insert the event and upsert the counter.\n- `usage_service` imports `src/repositories.usage_repo` to read the rollup.\n- Both services receive an authenticated `api_key_id` from the route handler (set by `require_api_key` guard).\n- `time_windows` is imported by `events_service` and `usage_service` to floor timestamps.\n\n**Transaction boundary:**\n- `create_event` wraps both the event insert and the rollup upsert in one PostgreSQL transaction (via `src/db/session_context`).\n- This atomicity ensures that if the insert wins (no existing `idempotency_key`), the counter increments exactly once.\n- If the insert loses (duplicate key), neither the counter nor any side effect happens — a no-op.","new_string":"**Public surface:**\n- Imported by `src/api.routes.{events, usage, quotas}` to execute the core business operations.\n\n**Dependencies:**\n- `events_service` imports `src/repositories.{events_repo, quotas_repo}` to insert the event, check the quota, and upsert the counter.\n- `usage_service` imports `src/repositories.usage_repo` to read the rollup.\n- `quota_service` imports `src/repositories.quotas_repo` to upsert the cap.\n- All three services receive an authenticated `AuthenticatedPrincipal` from the route handler (set by `require_api_key` guard); `principal.scope` gates `PUT /v1/quotas` at the route layer before `quota_service` ever runs.\n- `time_windows` is imported by `events_service` and `usage_service` to floor timestamps.\n\n**Transaction boundary:**\n- `create_event` wraps the event insert, the quota check, and the rollup upsert in one PostgreSQL transaction (via `src/db/session_context`).\n- This atomicity ensures that if the insert wins (no existing `idempotency_key`) and the quota check passes, the counter increments exactly once.\n- If the insert loses (duplicate key), the quota is never consulted and neither the counter nor any side effect happens — a no-op.\n- If the quota check rejects (`R + Q > L`), raising `QuotaExceededError` propagates out of the transaction context and rolls it back — the event insert is undone and the counter is never touched (no partial write).\n- `upsert_tenant_quota` wraps the quota upsert in its own transaction; a single `INSERT ... ON CONFLICT ... DO UPDATE ... RETURNING (xmax = 0)` reports create-vs-replace with no second round-trip."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":812,"cache_read_input_tokens":264649,"output_tokens":1065,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":812},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":1065,"cache_read_input_tokens":264649,"cache_creation_input_tokens":812,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":812,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcqBjmaroC6i8T8Vccphb","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"8e215bbf-43a5-476e-b0ce-e9f8daf30aa7","timestamp":"2026-07-08T20:01:33.235Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a