{"parentUuid":"04faa485-7c22-4a36-9162-1adfdf0d7db6","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"ce914322-90da-48cc-9778-0c7929bce84f","agentId":"aa3971c3406bc34d2","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01S3vF62ZdbEkkuT5PRGFKWm","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Implementation progress — per-customer metric quotas\n2\t\n3\tFollowing `.pipeline/tasks.md` (T1..T6), test-first per task. This file is\n4\tgitignored working state; terse notes only.\n5\t\n6\t## T1 — migration 0003 (quotas table + api_keys.scope)\n7\t- T1 done: tests written+red -> code -> green.\n8\t  Files: tests/integration/test_quota_migration.py,\n9\t  alembic/versions/0003_create_quotas_and_api_key_scope.py.\n10\t\n11\t## T2 — scope plumbing (api_keys_repo, AuthenticatedPrincipal, seed_api_key --admin)\n12\t- T2 done: tests written+red -> code -> green.\n13\t  Files: src/repositories/api_keys_repo.py (ApiKeyRecord.scope, create_api_key(scope=)),\n14\t  src/auth/api_key.py (AuthenticatedPrincipal.scope default \"ingest\", populated in verify_api_key),\n15\t  scripts/seed_api_key.py (--admin flag), tests/integration/test_seed_api_key_script.py::test_admin_flag_sets_scope.\n16\t  Verified existing tests/test_auth_api_key.py, test_events_endpoint.py, test_rate_limit.py,\n17\t  test_concurrency.py still green after the AuthenticatedPrincipal/ApiKeyRecord field additions.\n18\t  Next: T3 (schemas/quotas.py, quotas_repo.upsert_quota, quota_service, routes/quotas.py, errors.AppError, CORS PUT, mount router).\n19\t\n20\t## T3 — PUT /v1/quotas (upsert, admin scope, validation, error code, mount)\n21\t- T3 done: tests written+red -> code -> green.\n22\t  Files: tests/test_schemas_quotas.py, tests/integration/test_quotas_endpoint.py,\n23\t  src/api/schemas/quotas.py (QuotaPutRequest/QuotaResponse),\n24\t  src/repositories/quotas_repo.py (upsert_quota xmax idiom + read_tenant_quota_state_locked\n25\t  written now, consumed by T4), src/services/quota_service.py (upsert_tenant_quota,\n26\t  quota.upsert log, 201/200 mapping), src/api/routes/quotas.py (admin-scope gate,\n27\t  quota.forbidden log), src/api/errors.py (AppError + app_code honored in\n28\t  handle_http_exception), src/api/middleware.py (CORS allow_methods += PUT),\n29\t  src/main.py (mount quotas_router). Also extended test infra:\n30\t  tests/integration/conftest.py (make_api_key scope= param; truncate_tables\n31\t  includes quotas).\n32\t  Full suite green: 112 passed (tests/ minus k6 perf + unrelated dashboard tests).\n33\t  Next: T4 (read_tenant_quota_state_locked wiring into events_service quota\n34\t  check on the winning-insert branch; quota.rejected log;\n35\t  tests/integration/test_events_quota_enforcement.py).\n36\t\n37\t## T4 — POST /v1/events quota enforcement (FOR UPDATE read-and-decide)\n38\t- T4 done: tests written+red -> code -> green.\n39\t  Files: tests/integration/test_events_quota_enforcement.py,\n40\t  src/services/events_service.py (QuotaExceededError(AppError), quota check\n41\t  on the winning-insert branch using read_tenant_quota_state_locked, rollback\n42\t  on reject via raise-inside-transaction, quota.rejected log without totals,\n43\t  _seconds_until_next_hour_boundary for Retry-After).\n44\t  Full suite green: 120 passed (tests/ minus k6 perf + unrelated dashboard tests).\n45\t  Next: T5 (test_quota_concurrency.py -- N concurrent distinct-key posts never\n46\t  exceed L) and T6 (perf k6 quota scenario + DAST/docs) -- parallel-safe per\n47\t  tasks.md, doing T5 first then T6.\n48\t\n49\t## T5 — concurrency correctness (AC13)\n50\t- T5 done, but surfaced and fixed a real correctness bug in T4's\n51\t  `read_tenant_quota_state_locked` in the process (debugged empirically with\n52\t  scratch scripts, since removed): a single combined\n53\t  `SELECT ... LEFT JOIN usage_rollup ... FOR UPDATE OF q` does NOT give every\n54\t  concurrent waiter a fresh read of the joined `usage_rollup` row --\n55\t  PostgreSQL's `FOR UPDATE` only forces a fresh re-check (EvalPlanQual) of the\n56\t  LOCKED row itself; a joined, non-locked table is still read from the\n57\t  waiter's original (pre-wait) statement snapshot. Verified empirically: 20\n58\t  concurrent posts against a cap of 10 all read the same stale total and all\n59\t  got admitted (20/20 201s) -- the bug was invisible to the sequential T4\n60\t  tests (which never contend on the lock) and only showed up under real\n61\t  concurrency.\n62\t  FIX: split into two round-trips in the same transaction -- (1) lock the\n63\t  quotas row alone (`SELECT limit_per_window ... FOR UPDATE`, no join), then\n64\t  (2) a separate plain `SELECT total_quantity FROM usage_rollup ...` issued\n65\t  AFTER the lock is held, which gets its own fresh READ COMMITTED snapshot\n66\t  reflecting everything the previous lock holder just committed. Re-verified\n67\t  with the same empirical scripts: current_total now increases correctly\n68\t  across serialized waiters (0, 1, 2, ... capped at L) instead of staying\n69\t  stuck at 1 for every waiter.\n70\t  Files: tests/integration/test_quota_concurrency.py (new),\n71\t  src/repositories/quotas_repo.py (read_tenant_quota_state_locked rewritten\n72\t  as two statements; docstring documents the EvalPlanQual/snapshot subtlety\n73\t  and why a combined single-statement version is unsafe).\n74\t  Verified: test_quota_concurrency.py green across 3 repeated runs; full\n75\t  suite green (121 passed, tests/ minus k6 perf + unrelated dashboard tests)\n76\t  after the repo rewrite -- no regression to the T3/T4 sequential-path tests.\n77\t  Next: T6 (k6 quota-active perf scenario, DAST context, docs/READMEs/CLAUDE.md).\n78\t"}]},"uuid":"1a7b5c9b-655a-46b6-a0e6-a7dea8a85336","timestamp":"2026-07-08T20:07:23.510Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"04faa485-7c22-4a36-9162-1adfdf0d7db6","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","