{"parentUuid":"67c21450-4920-46e7-9e8e-1e2cada3a193","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa3971c3406bc34d2","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcqEz7r15WfqHt4pTQaSS","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01YGoixExwxs4K28ohd9G6hy","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\repositories\\README.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":424,"cache_read_input_tokens":305127,"output_tokens":130,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":424},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":130,"cache_read_input_tokens":305127,"cache_creation_input_tokens":424,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":424,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcqEz56Ywzxd4vScT6HxQ","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"0617f3f3-e46a-4234-a4c5-6e39767efe5f","timestamp":"2026-07-08T20:43:59.743Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"0617f3f3-e46a-4234-a4c5-6e39767efe5f","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"ce914322-90da-48cc-9778-0c7929bce84f","agentId":"aa3971c3406bc34d2","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01YGoixExwxs4K28ohd9G6hy","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# src/repositories/\n2\t\n3\t## Purpose\n4\t\n5\tData access layer: SQL queries with parameterization, row-level scoping (by authenticated `api_key_id`), and minimal-field projections. All database I/O is encapsulated here.\n6\t\n7\t## Modules\n8\t\n9\t| File / Module | Responsibility |\n10\t|---|---|\n11\t| `events_repo.py` | `create_or_replay_event(api_key_id, customer_id, metric, quantity, idempotency_key, window_start)` — INSERT ... ON CONFLICT ... DO NOTHING (idempotency). Also `upsert_rollup()` (called only on insert success). |\n12\t| `usage_repo.py` | `read_usage(api_key_id, customer_id, metric, window_start)` — SELECT from `usage_rollup` scoped by `api_key_id`. Returns None if missing (caller handles zero conversion). |\n13\t| `api_keys_repo.py` | `get_by_key_id(key_id)` — SELECT from `api_keys` by public `key_id` (used by auth cache miss). Returns the full row (id, key_id, secret_hash, rate_limit_per_sec, revoked_at). |\n14\t\n15\t## Relationships\n16\t\n17\t**Public surface:**\n18\t- Imported by `src/services.{events_service, usage_service}` to execute queries.\n19\t- `api_keys_repo` is also imported by `src/auth.api_key` (credential lookup on cache miss).\n20\t\n21\t**Dependencies:**\n22\t- All functions are async; they receive an `AsyncSession` from the service layer (obtained via `src/db.session_context`).\n23\t- Queries use SQLAlchemy ORM with bound parameters (no string concatenation); all user input is parameterized.\n24\t- RLS is set per-transaction by `src/db.session_context` before the first query runs (sets the `app.current_api_key_id` PostgreSQL context variable).\n25\t\n26\t**Row-level security:**\n27\t- Every query includes the authenticated `api_key_id` in the WHERE clause (primary application-layer control).\n28\t- E.g., `WHERE api_key_id = :auth_key AND customer_id = :customer_id` — no unscoped queries.\n29\t- PostgreSQL RLS policy (`USING (api_key_id = current_setting(...))`) is the backstop; the app role has no `BYPASSRLS`.\n30\t- If a query accidentally omits the `api_key_id` filter, RLS blocks it at the database level (defense-in-depth).\n31\t\n32\t**Field projections (minimal surface):**\n33\t- `create_or_replay_event` returns only `{event_id, customer_id, metric, quantity, window_start, idempotent_replay}` — not the full row (which includes `created_at`, `event_time`, `api_key_id`).\n34\t- `read_usage` returns only `{customer_id, metric, window_start, total_quantity, event_count}` — not internal bookkeeping (`updated_at`, `api_key_id`).\n35\t- `api_keys_repo.get_by_key_id` returns the full row (needed by auth for `secret_hash`, `rate_limit_per_sec`, `revoked_at`).\n36\t\n37\t**Constraint enforcement:**\n38\t- `create_or_replay_event` relies on the `UNIQUE (api_key_id, idempotency_key)` constraint at the DB level to detect duplicates.\n39\t- If a duplicate key is encountered, PostgreSQL raises an `IntegrityError` (caught by service layer) → the service reads the original row instead.\n40\t- `quantity > 0` and other domain constraints are enforced by CHECK constraints in the schema (verified at insert time).\n41\t\n42\t## Notes\n43\t\n44\t**ON CONFLICT pattern:**\n45\t- The idempotency mechanism uses `INSERT ... ON CONFLICT (api_key_id, idempotency_key) DO NOTHING RETURNING id, ...`.\n46\t- If the unique constraint is violated, the INSERT returns no rows.\n47\t- The service layer checks `if result` — if a row was returned, this request won the insert; if not, a duplicate is detected.\n48\t\n49\t**RLS context setup:**\n50\t- Before any query, `src/db.session_context` sets `SET LOCAL app.current_api_key_id = :id` in the transaction.\n51\t- This context variable is read by the PostgreSQL RLS policy on every table access.\n52\t- The `SET LOCAL` is per-transaction (automatically cleared at commit), so no context leakage across requests.\n53\t\n54\t**Async pattern:**\n55\t- All functions are async; they use `await session.execute(...)` for queries.\n56\t- They receive an `AsyncSession` that's already connected and in a transaction (setup by `src/db.session_context`).\n57\t- No explicit connection management in the repo; the session is provided by the caller.\n58\t"}]},"uuid":"4312d359-f788-41be-b697-a09bdd010519","timestamp":"2026-07-08T20:43:59.759Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"0617f3f3-e46a-4234-a4c5-6e39767efe5f","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"4312d359-f788-41be-b697-a09bdd010519","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa3971c3406bc34d2","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcqEzMKsMYf77a54cS8yB","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01VDBgwTtcj9ZLjEeFGcFAyA","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\repositories\\README.md","old_string":"| `events_repo.py` | `create_or_replay_event(api_key_id, customer_id, metric, quantity, idempotency_key, window_start)` — INSERT ... ON CONFLICT ... DO NOTHING (idempotency). Also `upsert_rollup()` (called only on insert success). |\n| `usage_repo.py` | `read_usage(api_key_id, customer_id, metric, window_start)` — SELECT from `usage_rollup` scoped by `api_key_id`. Returns None if missing (caller handles zero conversion). |\n| `api_keys_repo.py` | `get_by_key_id(key_id)` — SELECT from `api_keys` by public `key_id` (used by auth cache miss). Returns the full row (id, key_id, secret_hash, rate_limit_per_sec, revoked_at). |","new_string":"| `events_repo.py` | `create_or_replay_event(api_key_id, customer_id, metric, quantity, idempotency_key, window_start)` — INSERT ... ON CONFLICT ... DO NOTHING (idempotency). Also `upsert_rollup()` (called only on insert success). |\n| `usage_repo.py` | `read_usage(api_key_id, customer_id, metric, window_start)` — SELECT from `usage_rollup` scoped by `api_key_id`. Returns None if missing (caller handles zero conversion). |\n| `api_keys_repo.py` | `find_active_key_by_key_id(key_id)` — SELECT from `api_keys` by public `key_id` (used by auth cache miss); returns the full row including `scope`. `create_api_key(..., scope=\"ingest\")` — the only key-provisioning path. |\n| `quotas_repo.py` | `upsert_quota(...)` — `INSERT ... ON CONFLICT (api_key_id, customer_id, metric) DO UPDATE ... RETURNING (xmax = 0) AS inserted`, reporting create-vs-replace in one round-trip. `read_tenant_quota_state_locked(...)` — the atomic check-then-decide: locks the quota row (`FOR UPDATE`), then reads the current-window rollup total as a **separate, fresh** statement (see *Notes* below for why). Returns `None` when no quota exists (unlimited, no lock taken). |"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1780,"cache_read_input_tokens":305551,"output_tokens":929,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1780},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":929,"cache_read_input_tokens":305551,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1780,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1780,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcqEzKMJmU3bzpGxYWEnU","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"ae9b1d94-d9a5-4fc9-9571-c00c872a917f","timestamp":"2026-07-08T20:44:08.778Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
