{"parentUuid":"a7e06574-faeb-4c48-acc3-26b4e244c61e","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"ce914322-90da-48cc-9778-0c7929bce84f","agentId":"aa3971c3406bc34d2","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01B31YAXCypgWj8LMV48kMuz","type":"tool_result","content":"The file C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\repositories\\README.md has been updated successfully. (file state is current in your context — no need to Read it back)"}]},"uuid":"107b8de3-dd7a-470e-a4ff-544519ce35e9","timestamp":"2026-07-08T20:44:15.685Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"a7e06574-faeb-4c48-acc3-26b4e244c61e","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"107b8de3-dd7a-470e-a4ff-544519ce35e9","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa3971c3406bc34d2","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcqF1XM9RvDQ6uRGf3keH","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Qp4YNkxAHsiPdbEPMuTDj2","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\repositories\\README.md","old_string":"**RLS context setup:**\n- Before any query, `src/db.session_context` sets `SET LOCAL app.current_api_key_id = :id` in the transaction.\n- This context variable is read by the PostgreSQL RLS policy on every table access.\n- The `SET LOCAL` is per-transaction (automatically cleared at commit), so no context leakage across requests.\n\n**Async pattern:**","new_string":"**RLS context setup:**\n- Before any query, `src/db.session_context` sets `SET LOCAL app.current_api_key_id = :id` in the transaction.\n- This context variable is read by the PostgreSQL RLS policy on every table access.\n- The `SET LOCAL` is per-transaction (automatically cleared at commit), so no context leakage across requests.\n\n**Quota lock-then-read pattern (why it's two statements, not one):**\n- `read_tenant_quota_state_locked` deliberately issues the `FOR UPDATE` lock on `quotas` and the `usage_rollup` read as two separate statements, not a single `LEFT JOIN ... FOR UPDATE OF q` query.\n- PostgreSQL's `FOR UPDATE` only forces a fresh re-check (`EvalPlanQual`) of the *locked* row itself when a blocked waiter unblocks after the holder commits — it does **not** force a fresh snapshot for another table read in the same statement, including a joined one.\n- A single combined statement lets a waiter that queued before the holder committed read `usage_rollup` from its own stale pre-wait snapshot — verified empirically during implementation: every concurrent waiter read the same stale total and all got admitted, silently breaking the cap.\n- Issuing the `usage_rollup` read as its own statement *after* the lock is acquired gives it a fresh READ COMMITTED snapshot that does include everything the previous holder just committed — this is what makes `current_total` accurate for every waiter, not just the first uncontended caller (`tests/integration/test_quota_concurrency.py`).\n\n**Async pattern:**"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":429,"cache_read_input_tokens":308336,"output_tokens":833,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":429},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":833,"cache_read_input_tokens":308336,"cache_creation_input_tokens":429,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":429,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcqF1VN6DypmVEvDcW3Tt","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"3f39008a-ecfc-443b-83db-f518fdd27c7a","timestamp":"2026-07-08T20:44:24.519Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
