{"parentUuid":"a48fb579-974b-43c0-93e5-df3cf7f4a1a8","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa3971c3406bc34d2","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcqF2WwNWq9BcWWy2qK7f","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01GshEkDnegGX3EEAXjQDTe1","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\auth\\README.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1394,"cache_read_input_tokens":309674,"output_tokens":158,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1394},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":158,"cache_read_input_tokens":309674,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1394,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1394,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcqF2UMLr6PTR75aGe5nV","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"f765633e-2480-4dd5-8ef8-f8c45b6ce9f6","timestamp":"2026-07-08T20:44:32.495Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"f765633e-2480-4dd5-8ef8-f8c45b6ce9f6","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"ce914322-90da-48cc-9778-0c7929bce84f","agentId":"aa3971c3406bc34d2","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GshEkDnegGX3EEAXjQDTe1","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# src/auth/\n2\t\n3\t## Purpose\n4\t\n5\tAuthentication and authorization layer: API key verification (split-token parsing and Argon2id credential check), in-process verification cache for performance, and Redis-backed rate limiting (Tier-1 pre-auth and Tier-2 post-auth, both fail-open).\n6\t\n7\t## Modules\n8\t\n9\t| File / Module | Responsibility |\n10\t|---|---|\n11\t| `__init__.py` | `require_api_key` FastAPI dependency guard: parses the `Authorization: Bearer` header, checks the verification cache, falls back to DB lookup + Argon2id verify on cache miss, sets the authenticated `api_key_id` in request state. |\n12\t| `api_key.py` | Split-token key parsing (`mtr_live_<key_id>_<secret>`), verification logic (Argon2id check), cache TTL management, revocation status check. |\n13\t| `rate_limit.py` | Tier-1 (pre-auth, IP+route keyed) and Tier-2 (post-auth, api_key_id keyed) Redis token-bucket limiters; both fail open (log warning, allow request) on Redis connection error. |\n14\t\n15\t## Relationships\n16\t\n17\t**Public surface:**\n18\t- `require_api_key` is imported by `src/api.routes` as a FastAPI dependency (guard). When used, it populates `request.state.api_key_id` with the authenticated principal's ID.\n19\t- Tier-1 and Tier-2 rate limiters are called from `src/api.middleware` (Tier-1) and `src/api.routes.{events, usage}` (Tier-2).\n20\t\n21\t**Dependencies:**\n22\t- `api_key.py` imports `src.crypto` for Argon2id verify and `src.db.session_context` for credential lookup on cache miss.\n23\t- `api_key.py` imports `src.logging.get_logger` for debug/warning logs (e.g., revocation, cache miss).\n24\t- `rate_limit.py` imports `src.config.settings` for rate limits (per-key `rate_limit_per_sec`) and `src.redis_client` for token-bucket state.\n25\t- Both modules are async (return coroutines for use in async context).\n26\t\n27\t**Request flow:**\n28\t1. **Tier-1 throttle** (IP+route keyed) runs first in middleware, pre-auth. Checks Redis, fails open.\n29\t2. **`require_api_key`** parses and verifies the split token, caches verified keys.\n30\t3. **Tier-2 throttle** (api_key_id keyed) runs post-auth. Checks Redis with the now-authenticated principal's ID, fails open.\n31\t4. If any throttle rejects (rate limit exceeded), the handler never runs; 429 is returned.\n32\t\n33\t## Notes\n34\t\n35\t**Verification cache:**\n36\t- In-process TTL-bounded cache (default: 5 minutes) keyed on the public `key_id` (not the secret).\n37\t- On cache hit, constant-time comparison of the cached secret against the request secret (no Argon2id cost).\n38\t- On cache miss, DB lookup + Argon2id verify (expensive, ~100ms), then store in cache for future hits.\n39\t- Cache is per-process; horizontal scale-out (multiple Fargate tasks) means cache hit rates vary per task (not a correctness issue, just a performance variance).\n40\t\n41\t**Revocation:**\n42\t- API key lookup checks the `revoked_at` column; a non-null value means the key is revoked.\n43\t- Revoked keys are rejected with 403 and not cached.\n44\t- Cache invalidation is not real-time (revocations take up to 5 minutes to propagate across all tasks).\n45\t- Recorded in `.pipeline/plan.md` as an accepted risk (noted for future key-revocation SLA if tighter bounds are needed).\n46\t\n47\t**Rate limiting — fail-open behavior:**\n48\t- If Redis is unavailable, a Redis `ConnectionError` is caught and logged as a warning.\n49\t- The request is allowed through (traffic is not dropped).\n50\t- Recorded in `.pipeline/surface-delta.md` as an availability tradeoff: prefer dropping rate limits over dropping user requests.\n51\t\n52\t**Rate limiting — Tier-1 pre-auth:**\n53\t- Keyed on IP + route (e.g., `ratelimit:tier1:POST:/v1/events:192.0.2.1`).\n54\t- Limits apply per route (different budgets can be configured per route if needed).\n55\t- Protects against flooding *before* we pay an Argon2id cost.\n56\t- Runs in middleware; all routes inherit the same policy.\n57\t\n58\t**Rate limiting — Tier-2 post-auth:**\n59\t- Keyed on `api_key_id` (e.g., `ratelimit:tier2:123`).\n60\t- Limit is the key's `rate_limit_per_sec` column (default: 100 req/s).\n61\t- Per-customer isolation: two customers sharing one client IP each get independent buckets (discriminating test in `tests/integration/test_rate_limit.py`).\n62\t- Runs after auth in the route handler; only affects authenticated requests.\n63\t"}]},"uuid":"75e68f37-3e99-473b-ad6b-6439bd68dace","timestamp":"2026-07-08T20:44:32.511Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"f765633e-2480-4dd5-8ef8-f8c45b6ce9f6","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
{"parentUuid":"75e68f37-3e99-473b-ad6b-6439bd68dace","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa3971c3406bc34d2","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcqF2ocUausnQqgGYGxGN","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_015kuyeuQryuWW1duRVD4Zw8","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\auth\\README.md","old_string":"| `__init__.py` | `require_api_key` FastAPI dependency guard: parses the `Authorization: Bearer` header, checks the verification cache, falls back to DB lookup + Argon2id verify on cache miss, sets the authenticated `api_key_id` in request state. |\n| `api_key.py` | Split-token key parsing (`mtr_live_<key_id>_<secret>`), verification logic (Argon2id check), cache TTL management, revocation status check. |\n| `rate_limit.py` | Tier-1 (pre-auth, IP+route keyed) and Tier-2 (post-auth, api_key_id keyed) Redis token-bucket limiters; both fail open (log warning, allow request) on Redis connection error. |","new_string":"| `__init__.py` | `require_api_key` FastAPI dependency guard: parses the `Authorization: Bearer` header, checks the verification cache, falls back to DB lookup + Argon2id verify on cache miss, sets the authenticated `api_key_id` in request state. |\n| `api_key.py` | Split-token key parsing (`mtr_live_<key_id>_<secret>`), verification logic (Argon2id check), cache TTL management, revocation status check. `AuthenticatedPrincipal.scope` (`\"ingest\"` default, `\"admin\"` elevated) rides the same cached principal. |\n| `rate_limit.py` | Tier-1 (pre-auth, IP+route keyed) and Tier-2 (post-auth, api_key_id keyed) Redis token-bucket limiters; both fail open (log warning, allow request) on Redis connection error. |\n\n**Authorization scope (function-level, on top of authentication):**\n- `AuthenticatedPrincipal.scope` is `\"ingest\"` by default; `\"admin\"` is a superset scope, not a separate key family — an admin-scoped key does everything an ingest key does, plus is permitted to call `PUT /v1/quotas`.\n- Only `src/api/routes/quotas.py`'s composed dependency checks `scope` (`principal.scope == \"admin\"`, else `HTTPException(403)`); every other route ignores it, so existing behavior is unchanged.\n- Provisioned via `scripts/seed_api_key.py --admin` (defaults to `\"ingest\"` without the flag); this is also the DAST-context admin test key (DAST-3)."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1928,"cache_read_input_tokens":311068,"output_tokens":946,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1928},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":946,"cache_read_input_tokens":311068,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1928,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1928,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcqF2jRx97SJ3ELjjxCjT","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"5b8bd248-1fc6-4626-8d75-fba8433c4ced","timestamp":"2026-07-08T20:44:43.149Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/metric-quotas"}
