{"parentUuid":"358098ab-aa69-4846-bcbb-f21c17d63064","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aa3971c3406bc34d2","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccqag59bym9FXUymagcLp","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Summary\n\nImplemented `.pipeline/plan.md` (per-customer metric quotas) task-by-task per `.pipeline/tasks.md` (T1–T6), test-first throughout.\n\n**What was built:**\n- **T1** — Migration `alembic/versions/0003_create_quotas_and_api_key_scope.py`: `quotas` table (PK `(api_key_id, customer_id, metric)`, `CHECK(limit_per_window >= 1)`, RLS policy) + `api_keys.scope` column (`CHECK IN ('ingest','admin')`).\n- **T2** — `scope` plumbing: `src/repositories/api_keys_repo.py`, `src/auth/api_key.py` (`AuthenticatedPrincipal.scope`), `scripts/seed_api_key.py --admin`.\n- **T3** — `PUT /v1/quotas`: `src/api/schemas/quotas.py`, `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py` (`upsert_quota`, xmax idiom), `src/services/quota_service.py`, `src/api/routes/quotas.py` (admin-scope gate), `src/api/errors.py` (`AppError` + `app_code`), CORS `PUT`, mounted in `src/main.py`.\n- **T4** — Quota enforcement wired into `src/services/events_service.py` on the winning-insert branch (`QuotaExceededError`, rollback-on-reject, `Retry-After`).\n- **T5** — Concurrency test (`tests/integration/test_quota_concurrency.py`) **surfaced and fixed a real correctness bug**: a single `LEFT JOIN usage_rollup ... FOR UPDATE OF q` statement does not give concurrent waiters a fresh read of the joined table (PostgreSQL's `FOR UPDATE` only re-checks the locked row itself). Fixed by splitting `read_tenant_quota_state_locked` in `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py` into two round-trips (lock the quota row, then a fresh separate rollup read) — verified empirically and via the concurrency test.\n- **T6** — k6 quota-active perf scenario (`tests/integration/k6/load_events_quota.js` + new fixture/test in `tests/integration/test_perf_k6_load.py`), doc updates (`docs/system_architecture.md`, `src/api/README.md`, `src/services/README.md`, `src/repositories/README.md`, `src/auth/README.md`, `CLAUDE.md`).\n\n**Environment issue found and fixed (test infra only):** running the full suite together intermittently hit `TooManyConnectionsError` once a third heavy multi-worker-uvicorn perf fixture was added; fixed by raising the shared testcontainer's `max_connections` in `tests/integration/conftest.py` (`with_command(\"postgres -c max_connections=300\")`) — not a production change.\n\n**Final state:** all AC1–AC21 covered by tests (AC22 correctly delegated to security per `acceptance.md`); full suite green twice in a row (124 passed). `.pipeline/surface-delta.md` and `.pipeline/implementation-progress.md` written.\n\nKey files: `C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\alembic\\versions\\0003_create_quotas_and_api_key_scope.py`, `src\\repositories\\quotas_repo.py`, `src\\services\\events_service.py`, `src\\services\\quota_service.py`, `src\\api\\routes\\quotas.py`, `src\\api\\schemas\\quotas.py`, `src\\api\\errors.py`, `tests\\integration\\test_quota_concurrency.py`, `tests\\integration\\test_events_quota_enforcement.py`, `tests\\integration\\test_quotas_endpoint.py`, `tests\\integration\\test_quota_migration.py`, `tests\\test_schemas_quotas.py`, `docs\\system_architecture.md`, `.pipeline\\surface-delta.md`, `.pipeline\\implementation-progress.md`."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":592,"cache_read_input_tokens":324353,"output_tokens":1368,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":592},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":1368,"cache_read_input_tokens":324353,"cache_creation_input_tokens":592,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":592,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"